london.name: Richard Sen
london.description:
'Sporadic, wild and free he has never been one to be tamed, placed in a box and told how to play. From his youthful days spent painting the mean streets of London through to his acid laden take on old school club music he has amassed a reputation as one of the best in Britain' (Ransom Note 2018).

Fetish clubs and festivals; dark basements and back rooms; disco pubs and super-clubs. Richard has done it all, globally. His authenticity, experience and 30 year history in dance music map out a unique story.

Richard began DJing in 1989 with a residency at the infamous Crazy Club at Busbys and The Astoria (London). Ecstasy, acid house and frequent trips to New York, visiting his heroes at Nu Groove and Strictly Rhythm and searching for Chicago obscurities and Loft classics, provided the catalyst for Richard's dance music addiction. In 1993, Sen began working as a music buyer at the iconic London second-hand record shop, Music and Video Exchange. Since then he has amassed a vast collection and is recognised as an elder statesman, an educator and one of the leading experts of dance music in the world.

Richard's genre-fluid selection seamlessly flows back and forth between: old and new; dark and light; retro and futuristic disco, Italo, wonky house, electro, breakbeat and deep techno.

Sen has played all over the world in the past 30 years, including legendary clubs such as Sabresonic, Blood Sugar and Haywire (Andrew Weatherall’s club nights during the 90s and 2000s), Sign of the Times (UK 90s), Heavenly Social (UK 90s), Fabric (London), Sub Club (Glasgow), Robert Johnson (Germany), Air (Tokyo), D-Edge (Sao Paulo) and Cielo (NYC), and festivals including, Creamfields (UK), The Big Chill (UK), Pukkelpop (Belgium), 10 Days Off (Belgium) and Vibes on a Summer's Day (Australia).

Sen turned his talents to music production and recording in 1997. He has released more recently under his own name and under the guises of Bronx Dogs (1997-2003) and Padded Cell (2005-2012). He has released singles on his own label, Darkness Is Your Candle and for like-minded labels, Klasse Wrecks, Emotional Especial and Public Release. Sen's remix and production work have included respected artists such as: Bryan Ferry, John Grant, Unloved (David Holmes' band), LCD Soundsystem, Saint Etienne and The Jungle Brothers. Padded Cell's 'Signal Failure' single was also chosen by Francois Kevorkian to be used in the biggest selling video game of all time - Grand Theft Auto 4. Their music was also used in the U.S. HBO comedy show Eastbound and Down. In 2012, Richard released a compilation, This Ain't Chicago on Strut Records. This was a ground-breaking selection of obscure, early UK house music, widely regarded as the first retrospective of its kind. The promo video was listed in Beatport's top ten house documentaries of all time.

Richard remains passionate yet professional with impeccable taste. He currently has a bi-monthly radio show for Charlie Bones' station, Do!! You!!! (www.doyou.world) which allows him to narrate his history, explore his vast collection and introduce his eclectic taste to a new generation. 

Still a fan at heart, his favourite DJs who have inspired him, who he has gained support and respect from, and who have played his music include: David Mancuso, DJ Harvey, Andrew Weatherall and 'Evil' Eddie Richards.

london.name: Colleen Cosmo Murphy
london.description:
Colleen ‘Cosmo’ Murphy is a highly respected and experienced musical selector, DJ, radio host and curator, founder of the album listening event and content hub Classic Album Sundays and an authority on music, sound and the vinyl renaissance.
 
She was mentored by David Mancuso at his seminal Loft parties in New York City. Together they co-produced the compilation series David Mancuso Presents The Loft and worked together on David’s record label The Loft Audiophile Library of Music. In 2000, David told Time Out New York City “She is very devoted and very pure about the music. She’s one of the only people I would trust, both with the music and with the equipment, to fill in for me.” She was asked by David to help manage his legacy and continues to be one of the musical hosts at The Loft in NYC. She is also the co-founder of the Lucky Cloud Loft parties in London and DJs internationally on the world's best sound systems and dance floors.

Colleen hosts Cosmodelica, a monthly radio show on Worldwide FM selected by Time Out as one of the 10 best shows in London. She is now bringing Cosmodelica to the dancefloor to high-end audio venues like London’s Giant Steps and New York City’s Public Records. In March she is hosting a Cosmodelica residency at the Prince of Wales with special guests.

In 2019 Colleen was nominated into the DJ Mag North America Hall of Fame and launched Love Dancin’ Sound System at Gilles Peterson’s We Out Here Festival, sharing some of her musical and sonic passions to dancers outside of her existing communities to rave reviews. She will once again host the Love Dancin’ tent at We Out Here in 2020.

In the last few years Colleen has brought her uplifting musical energy to other festivals including Houghton where she has hosted a marathon set every year since its inception and is returning in 2020. She has played alongside Gilles Peterson for his closing party at his Worldwide Festival, a headline closing set at Dekmantel Selectors 2019 and sets at Kala Festival, Lost Village, One Day at the Disco, Flow Festival and Umbria Jazz Festival.

She hosted one of the most popular disco sets for Boiler Room and has recently been featured as the subject of a podcast for Resident Advisor. DJ Mag UK featured a lengthy long-read article about her in August 2019.

 Her Classic Album Sundays platform tells the stories behind the albums that have shaped our culture and in some cases, our lives. Colleen founded Classic Album Sundays as a stance against the increasing devaluation of music and sound. What began as a passion project is now the world’s most popular album listening event with satellites in four continents and the website and social media channels host content on classic albums and artists such as interviews, videos, playlists and more. BBC Breakfast Television remarked, “Classic Album Sundays treat our best-loved records like great symphonies.” She has hosted events with amazing talent such as Jarvis Cocker, Guy Garvey, Laura Mvula, Max Richter, John Grant, Pink Floyd’s Nick Mason and many more.
 
Colleen has been a radio host, DJ and programme director since the age of fourteen and today hosts Cosmodelica and Classic Album Sundays Worldwide on Worldwide FM and ‘This Women’s Work’ series for Public Radio International. She is the writer and host of BBC 6 Music’s album series ‘Sounds of a City’ and BBC Radio 4’s doc series ‘Turntable Tales’. Unfold Japan, a radio series she hosted for Worldwide FM and Asahi, has recently been nominated for an ARIA Award (Audio and Radio Industry Awards).

london.name: Anthony James
london.description:
Born and raised in East London, Anthony James has developed his sound with influences from the gritty city and the percussive and soulful world music introduced to him through his culturally diverse heritage. Learning to play music from the age of 7, producing since 16 and DJing since 18 has led him to play a mix of Afro House & Afro Tech adorned with hints of Deep, Soulful, Latin and Tech house.

His productions are built around dramatic ambient soundscapes, discerning arpeggiated synths, emotive piano chords & riffs and distinct percussion from around the world. His passion as a classically trained pianist and a fascination with fine art and psychology fuel intricate and intentionally experimental compositions.

Anthony's DJ Career started around 2013 with sets in Shoreditch, not far from where he grew up, to Brixton when he re-located to the heart of South London. Exploring his love for deep house, he went on to play at venues such as Studio338, Egg Ldn, Tape (Members), The Steelyard, Ministry of Sound and overseas in Spain, Netherlands and Greece. His residencies in Londons nightlife circuit and around Mayfair gave him the opportunity to further diversify his musical palate at venues such as Tape, MNKY HSE, Aqua, W Hotel, Raffles and many more.

in 2020, he delved into the world of radio broadcasting, joining the Select Radio team. His weekly show, Audiotherapy, has garnered support from some of the biggest names across the Afro House & Electronic Music scene - such as Themba, Kasango, Atmos Blaq, Enoo Napa, Aluku Rebels, John Summit and Karyendasoul. a behind-the-scenes view implies that there are plenty of big things on the horizon for the 29-year-old.

london.name: MOODENA
london.description:
Co-Owner / Producer & DJ @TropicalDiscoRecords
DJ bookings: ed@arcade-talent.com

Moodena’s success over the last five years has been nothing short of prodigious. His meteoric rise to being ever present at the pinnacle of both the disco & Nu Disco charts has seen him become one of the most in demand DJ/ producers across the globe. Delving a little deeper, Moodena has in fact earned his disco stripes the hard way, through nearly 30 years of non-stop efforts working in the music industry. Notably, he was co-founder of the hugely influential MN2S, an independent trailblazer in all aspects of the electronic music industry,running events, a DJ Agency/Management and Label distribution. In 2018, Moodena brought that incredible industry experience to Tropical Disco Records, developing the label into one of the most influential labels powering Disco’s current renaissance. Moodena has built an insatiable following along the way for his releases, with legendary selectors regularly supporting his work including Dave Lee FK Joey Negro, Folamour, Danny Krivit, Chez Damier, Louie Vega, Kenny Dope and Soul Clap to name a few. 

Over the last few years there have been a landslide of chart bound releases and accolades for both Moodena and Tropical Disco, who were label of the year at the OGV awards in 2021. Moodena has clocked up multiple best producer nominations and more than 25 Traxsource genre No 1’s and 70+ Top 10’s alongside millions of streams on Spotify. He was also crowned Traxsource Nu Disco Atist Of The Year two years in a row 2019 and 2020. Moodena’s chart-topping qualities have also seen him become hugely sought after as a remixer with recent stand out remixes for Dave Lee on Z Records, Rhyze and John Davis, both on legendary New York label Nervous, ‘The Destroyer’ for Soul Central, and Bellaire’s ‘Sunset Ballad’.

Despite such impressive studio prowess Moodena is perhaps most at home in the DJ booth, seamlessly combining everything from Disco and US Garage to house and Techno. His ability to fully connect with the crowd have seen him play everywhere from Elrow’s Festival in Croatia to Printworks in London to Soho House in Rome and Istanbul, Curfew Festival in Belgium and Heidegluhen in Berlin, one of the globes quintessential underground tastemaker clubs. He has also toured extensively in Mexico and toured India for the first time in October 2023.  His stand-out Moodena Presents nights have become London staples booking legends and upstarts alike, including Dave Lee (AKA Joey Negro), The Shapeshifters, Kirollus, Young Pulse, Ray Mang, Mighty Mouse (RIP), CJ Mackintosh, Art of Tones to name a few. With Moodena currently back in the studio working his magic on a fresh batch of disco classics and multiple international tours already confirmed it’s safe to say that his success will continue for many years to come. 

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/MOODENA909/
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/moodena909/
Soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/moodena
Traxsource: https://www.traxsource.com/artist/449455/moodena

london.name: Eurielle
london.description:
From an idyllic, leafy Yorkshire upbringing and a lifetime dedicated to classical training comes Eurielle.

After graduating from a vocal scholarship with St. Peter’s School in York, Eurielle spent two years preparing to audition for the three major classical music conservatoires in London, and also became a member of the National Youth Choir of Great Britain. Eurielle accepted a vocal scholarship for the Bachelor of Music Course at The Royal Academy of Music in 2007. Under the esteemed, late Noelle Barker OBE at the Academy, Eurielle explored her musical range and started to develop the sound which would later become her trademark – a classically infused but modern musical take on the stories of mythology, legend, fantasy and our own human nature.

Whilst still at college, in 2010, Eurielle was introduced to multi-platinum producer Ryan Louder (who has also worked with Dido, Katherine Jenkins, Pixie Lott and Anastasia). Ryan and Eurielle saw in each other the perfect musical match and they began to co-write and record together. This resulted in the production of Eurielle’s debut album, “Arcadia” which she self-released in December 2015, and the pair have collaborated on a number of singles which they have released since too.

Following this, in 2018 Eurielle was introduced to songwriter and leading film & TV soundtrack composer, Charlie Mole whose credits include writing songs for Kylie Minogue and Chaka Khan, and soundtracks for ‘Mr Selfridge’, ‘The Importance of Being Earnest’, ‘Othello’, ‘Dorian Gray’, and ‘The Sopranos’. This introduction led to Eurielle collaborating with Charlie on her second and third studio albums, both of which they co-wrote and co-produced together. Entitled “Goodbye Butterfly” and “Lady In Waiting” (respectively), these albums were recorded and produced at the very highest level; under the baton of Alastair King on both occasions, the Chamber Orchestra Of London and RSVP Voices were recorded in world renowned Lyndhurst Hall – AIR Studios, London, with veteran engineer Paul Golding in charge of capturing the recordings and mixing and mastering them afterwards. Eurielle released both albums independently in December 2019 and October 2021 respectively.

To date, Eurielle has built up a substantial catalogue of releases which have attracted a large fan base online, with millions of views and streams of her recordings and videos on both YouTube and Spotify. Her work has already earned her the recognition and endorsement of BBC Introducing, and playlist placement on national classical music radio station, Scala Radio as well as one of Spotify’s own official curated playlists, and several of her songs have been sampled by internationally famous artists and DJs including American hip-hop trio, Migos, and Hardstyle legends – Headhunterz, Wildstylez and Sound Rush.

Her natural ability to connect with her voice, coupled with a pure simplicity of tone has subsequently resulted in strong demand for her vocals for high profile film, TV and video game soundtracks from pre-eminent composers including John Lunn, Nicholas Hooper, Benjamin Wallfisch, Daniel Pemberton, Ben Foster, David Schweitzer, Barnaby Taylor and Michael Gordon Shapiro, seeing Eurielle record for the likes of Downton Abbey, Disney, the BBC, the Rio Paralympics 2016, Kaleidoscope Pictures, 20th Century Fox, Universal Pictures, Shazam! (New Line Cinema: Warner Brothers), Enola Holmes (Netflix), and Dice Legacy (DESTINYbit) already.

Looking ahead, Eurielle has several more major soundtrack projects in the pipeline and notable collaborations planned, as well as the creation of further albums of her own, so sign up to her mailing list via her website if you’d like to be notified about her future releases here: https://eurielle.com/

london.name: mixmastermorris
london.description:
Started Dj-ing in 80s at indie gigs and then on pirate radio/tv station Network 21. Opened his first club in 1985, Toured as DJ with The Shamen, then signed with Rising High Records for the albums Flying High, Global Chillage. Joined up with Pete Namlook to record two albums as Dreamfish. Did two sessions for BBC's John Peel. Residencies at underground clubs like Lost and Megatripolis. Remixed Coldcut's Autumn Leaves which went on to become a classic. Played at Love Parade and Glastonbury festival throughout the 90s. 

Wrote for NME, Mixmag and i-D magazine, presented The Chill Out Zone on Kiss FM.Toured Europe, USA and Japan repeatedly, made mix CDs like The Morning After, Abstract Funk Theory, God Bless The Chilled. Signed with Ninja Tunes and made the album Its Tomorrow Already and singles Nepalese Bliss & Fish Dances. Got involved with the Big Chill at the very beginning in 1994 and played every year since for them. Appeared in the cult movie Modulations. Recorded an album in Japan with Jonah Sharp and Harry Hosono of YMO. Made a TV commercial, soundtracked a play on Radio 3 and remixed the Dr Who theme for the BBC. Talked about Brian Eno on C4. Moved his Nubient club to Big Chill Bar. Won Ibiza Chillout DJ of the year - twice. Did two mixes for Rob da Banks show on Radio 1. Remixed Anne Garner and 6th Sense. Made an Altermodern podcast for the Tate Britain.  2010 won Best Downtempo DJ again, and started new job running Apollo label as part of R+S...

london.name: weareanathema
london.description:
This is the sound of music with real meaning, from a band growing in popularity against all the odds. A band defying expectations and rewriting the rule books on what can and can't be done in rock music. A band with such a natural sense of melody, balanced with seething power and lyrics that enlighten and inspire, a band of brothers and sisters, a band of unique origin. This is the best band you have never heard of. This album is beyond anything you ever heard before in its field. We are Anathema: we're here because we're here.

Anathema returned on May 31st with their new album, We're Here Because We're Here. Described as  ‘A flawless, life-affirming comeback and a gold-plated contender for album of the year’  and given a 9/10 review by Classic Rock, this is the first collection of new material from the band since the 2003 album, A Natural Disaster. A multi-coloured, multi-layered work of unbridled emotion, passion, and intensity, the new album has been embraced by their legions of fans and worldwide press.

‘We’re Here Because We’re Here is the finest they have unleashed so far... a stunningly enjoyable album.’ Classic Rock Prog.

Formed in Liverpool in 1990, the band’s sound and musical vision has continually evolved over the ensuing years while always remaining true to the band’s original goal of creating forward-thinking, meaningful, passionate, and honest music. With each release they moved beyond the boundaries of limited scenes and pigeon holes, creating a complex and emotive atmospheric sound. The album has been mixed by Steven Wilson (Porcupine Tree), who has described it as “definitely among the best albums I've ever had the pleasure to work on.”

‘It’s been seven years coming but Anathema’s eighth studio is very much worth the wait... Getting mixed by Porcupine Tree’s Steven Wilson is a fitting honour for such a splendidly built record’ 9/10 Metal Hammer.

Anathema have been at the forefront of the UK rock/metal movement for many years. They began their journey as pioneers of melodic heavy music, influencing a myriad of bands to follow them, before outgrowing all genres and limitations as they fearlessly explored new territory and new ways to express feeling through sound.
The line-up is really a collective of two families who were quite simply born to do it. Anathema consists of brothers Vincent, Daniel and Jamie Cavanagh, alongside childhood friends John Douglas and his sister Lee, who is an incredible singer in her own right. The line-up is completed by Les Smith, who brings much in the way of production expertise to the band.
There is a deeper bond in the group that transcends usual band politics, ego, and self-interest. They have a shared vision: to make the most incredible music they possibly can, and it seems, despite the lavish praise heaped on the band for their past work, that they are now taking their work to a whole new level.


ANATHEMA - WE'RE HERE BECAUSE WE'RE HERE
‘a glittering masterclass in atmospheric rock’ 9/10 Terrorizer


‘A flawless, life-affirming comeback and a gold-plated contender for album of the year’ 9/10 Classic Rock

‘A dazzling collection of highly-charged, progressive and emotively atmospheric rock songs that rarely dip below the euphoric.’ Rocksound

‘We’re Here Because We’re Here is the finest they have unleashed so far... a stunningly enjoyable album.’ Classic Rock Prog

‘Scouse progsters make a spectacular return... makes a seven year wait feel entirely worth it’ KKKK Kerrang!

‘the mighty Anathema, are back after a seven year recording hiatus with their latest record, the beautiful We’re Here Because We’re Here, and it’s one of the most ethereal pieces of music the band have produced... a welcome return indeed’ * * * * * Big Cheese

‘Anathema are a hidden jewel in the UK’s prog crown.  Their finest album to date... it’s an uplifting and sonically sumptuous rock record that could hardly be more appropriate for these prog-loving times’ Metal Hammer 

‘Everything modern-day Anathema fans will want and embrace: beautifully crafted, emotionally-charged and modern melodic rock of the highest order’ 9/10 Powerplay

‘the results are nothing short of breathtaking’ 4.5/5 Blunt

k_schreiber is a London based producer with a passion for underground electronic music. 

Nurtured on a diet of soul, funk and hip hop, his musical horizons were broadened by John Peel and Gilles Peterson leading to a vinyl obsession that persists to this day.

Having earned his stripes as a DJ and promoter in the underground London music scene, it was only a matter of time before his love of moving the crowd paved the way for a natural progression into music making.

london.name: Vernham Chronicles (John Saunders)
london.description: My name is John Saunders, I am a songwriter and musician (for want of a better terminology) and I am the author of 'The Vernham Chronicles' my first novel. This page is a place where I shall be uploading songs and instrumentals that are designed to accompany an audio version of my book should the opportunity arise. There are 3 instrumentals here not connected with The Vernham Chronicles and come from my murky past as part of an ongoing body of work called 'Filmless Soundtracks' that hails from the early 1980s. The Vernham Chronicles’, John Saunders’ first book, is a charming light comedy with a schoolboy sense of humour that is perhaps a little dark around the edges at times, it features twelve chapters, ten of which detail a day or event in the life throughout a year of a little fantasy village called Vernham. Two chapters are dedicated to complete and utter nonsense, one recounting characters and events of Vernham past (Of Idiosyncrasies, Ideas and Idiots), the other details the farcical happenings in the Vernham native’s lives (Vernham Gossip Update). ‘The Vernham Chronicles’ confuses fact with fiction, merging historical events with complete fabrication. It is written as a narrative in the present tense, with the odd recycled joke, in a children’s story style which is often sarcastic, and the occasional digression and flashback to previous events that explain the reasons behind the current situation. The little village of Vernham, buried deep in the Vernbury Vale, is a hive of activity with its natives going about their everyday business in sometimes less than conventional ways. Almost frozen in time, where its populace struggle to come to terms with the modern day, Vernham village refuses to recognise the £1 coin, only £1 notes are accepted in its shops. For visitors to Vernham, or ‘Spruggles’ as the Vernhamites call them, the £1 notes are printed in the city of Busted at the back of a Bureau de Change, where the exchange rate is £1.20p to £1 note, and when the need to change notes back to coins arises you’ll only get 80p in return for your £1 note. The characters are all a bit odd, there is the local Bobby PC Fred Sweetman who has a strange habit which is revealed in chapter two, a Fire Chief that is irresponsible with matches, Mrs Bunkerton who’s been recently widowed seven years ago as she tells everybody every day, she also suffers from a strange obsessive compulsive disorder and irritable bowel syndrome, but we won’t mention too much about the latter. A very alcoholic Reverend Parsworthy, always collecting for the Church door fund, and spending the proceeds in the local pub ’The Grummet and Nut’, the door never gets bought. And the star ‘Mr Robson the counterfeit Scotsman’, seemingly ubiquitous and irritating, convinced of his Scottish ancestry and past lives after he had a dream about Rabbie Burns, which he wrongly refers to as his ‘post monition‘, a warning after the event. Mr Robson of course has always been a Vernhamite, as were all of his ancestors, he’s quite mad. The final chapter sees Mr Robson realising his Celtic dream at a Christmas party, in a sad but very sweet way. http://www.amazon.co.uk/Vernham-Chronicles-John-Saunders/dp/1907499598/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1317379163&sr=1-1 Vernham Chronicles Create your badge

london.name: Somersault
london.description:
Labels:
PIV / Gruuv / Pitch / META / MadTech / Rawsome Deep /  Sit Down / Airtime / Whoyostro / Innocent Music / Hidden Vibes / Subsonic / Suprematic /  Bonzai Progressive / Ugenius / Bassic / Open Records / Upon Access

When introducing Somersault it’s best to let the music do the talking. From chart-topping releases on PIV, Gruuv and META, to being remixed by Jimpster and Audiojack. Heads are turning fast to this thriving force from down under.
 
Heavily influenced by jazz-infused house, the shuffling rhythms of UK garage and rolling atmospheric techno, Somersault straddles the line between delirious highs and murky lows, with a sound that’s brought his unique sets to some of the most respected outdoor festivals and underground clubs.
 
The talented producer has come a long way from session guitarist to forging a signature brand of completely unique and enduring, groove focussed music. Receiving support from Archie Hamilton, Stacey Pullen, Prunk, Tobi Neumann, Groove Armada, John Digweed, Felix Da Housecat, Laurent Garnier, Karotte, Roger Sanchez, Franky Rizardo, the list goes on and on.
 
Finding creative comfort in a raw stripped back sound, Somersault’s recent releases have been signed to world-renowned imprints: Kerri Chandler’s MadTech, Rawsome Deep, Airtime, Whoyostro, Sit Down and Innocent. His genre-bending work has also been snatched up by Suprematic, Hidden Vibes, Bassic and Open.
 
From dimly lit clubs to sun-drenched festival floors, Somersault seizes the psyche of the party. His lively DJ performances have seen him perform at Amsterdam Dance Event and become a festival regular at Rabbits Eat Lettuce, Subsonic, Dragon Dreaming and Elements, along with famed brands on the club circuit: Revolver Upstairs, Goodbar, S.A.S.H and Elsewhere.

london.name: Koster
london.description:
KOSTER realised his 
first love for House music back in 1995. In 2002, he moved to London where he 
acquired much experience in the music industry. Koster was involved in the underground music circuit at London
clubs, including; Ministry of Sound, Egg, Lightbox, Koko, Fire, Brixton Academy, Electric 
Brixton, to name a few. His musical agility made him widely acknowledged in the 
London music scene and went on to highlight guest slots warming up for Carl Cox in London 
at Electric Brixton, for Miguel Campbel at Bootleg Social’s showcase at Sankeys in Ibiza, 
spinning for the Cafe del Mar tour in Brazil and to an audience of thousands of people at the 
Together Winter Music Festival alongside John Digweed, Pete Tong 
among others.
KOSTER first made an impact on the deejaying scene through his DJ/producer duo, 
M!5CHIEFZ. Resulting in his music being played and supported by big names in the scene such as Marco Carola, Black Coffee, Paco Osuna, Leftwing-Kody, Renato Cohen, Stacey Pullen, Luigi Madonna, to name a few. M!5CHIEFZ was honored 
to perform twice at the iconic Space Ibiza, plus gigs from London to Portugal, Brazil and 
beyond.
Currently, with over 15 years of experience in the art of deejaying and producing, Koster is
determined to focus on his new project. He has been 
spending loads of time in the studio, working on music that is contorted with elements of 
House, a hint of progressive melodic atmospheres, groovy drums and a
fierce bass line that have bestowed support from massive names in the industry such as Joseph Capriati, Marco Carola, Richie Hawtin, Paco Osuna, Paul Van Dyk, Joachim Garraud to name a few.
Be sure to check out his forthcoming releases.

london.name: Uakoz
london.description:
BIO:

Developing a strong passion for music from a very early age, The Italian started self-teaching himself how to play drum machines and exploring free music software after being hypnotized to Techno and Minimal beats. 

Having built music production skills in his hometown, in 2011 he decided to join the SAE Institute in Milan in order to sharpen his technical skills and deepen his knowledge in this matter. 

With a full set of new skills acquired through both studying and playing his very first international gigs immediately after getting outside his own city, Uakoz moved to London (where he has been based since 2013) to pursue his dream of developing his music career and broaden his musical perceptions.

With constant work and dedication, he signed music on some remarkable labels such as Kneaded Pains, Elevate, Terminal M, Bedrock Records, Planet Rhythm, KMS, and OFF Recordings, among many others. 
Moreover, His music has been played and supported by renowned veterans in the dance music scene such as Carl Cox, Drumcell, Kevin Saunderson, Chris Liebing, Pig&Dan, John Digweed. Adam Beyer, Ida Engberg, Chus & Ceballos, Paul Ritch, KaiserDisco, Juliet Fox, Ramon Tapia, Mattia Trani, Enrico Sangiuliano, T78, Spartaque, Dr Motte, Dubspeeka, Karotte, Ron Costa and more. 

Behind the decks, he has demonstrated, numerous times, his finely honed skills as a result of years of dedication. His musical journey has taken him to diverse corners of the globe, from Bahrain to Los Angeles, Berlin to Amsterdam, Nantes to Split. Within London, he's left his mark on esteemed venues such as E1, Outernet, and EGG, while also making waves outside the capital, including the likes of Wire Club in Leeds and Liquor Club in Lincoln.

Undoubtedly an eclectic artist in a perpetual state of evolution, boasting indisputable skills and profound knowledge across various musical domains.

london.name: John TC Ashdown
london.description:
"JOHN TC's BITTERSWEET VENEERS" is a complete new album released on the 29/11/2022.
Lyrically the album is largely fueled by childhood memories of South London and past and present railway history. It also briefly touches on the dark side of human nature in relationships, boorish behavior and "Under a Lockdown Sky" states the obvious.
Musically the album offers a cross between pop, rock, progressive, blues and folk styles, late sixties beat and marks a personal comeback from a hand injury sustained from last year.
Release date: 29/11/2022.
 
 ABOUT JOHN TC ASHDOWN:
Having the first, second, third and forth of many final cracks of getting my sounds out into the world. May go for a fifth too.. Well you never know!

Always loved music, started off on keyboards before discovering the beautiful guitar sounds of John Williams at 15 years old. 
Songwriting followed at 18, 21 was the first live performance.

First proper band was a quartet called Agent's Estate, mostly featured original material.

Had my first proper original band at the age of 23, in which we wrote songs with strong melodies. I like to think that has stayed with me to this day, the years of listening to the Beatles, Kinks, Stones, Hollies, Jethro Tull, Yes, Stranglers, Pink Floyd, Squeeze, Beautiful South, Dire Straits, Joe Jackson, David Bowie etc. Paying off in some way.

The ensuing years after has mostly been that of a bread-and-butter musician, from playing other people’s music in lots of different settings, with lots of highs and lows-some of the highlights were backing the Drifters when they toured over here, to playing cabaret shows backing winners from Stars-in-their-eyes and Cabaret shows with Brian Conley.

But now here we are again with the original stuff, this time as a DIAY man (do it ALL yourself😂)Oh and check out Stone Park Avenue here too, my last originals band I was in. Big highlight there was playing a rock festival in 2016-held in the middle of a prestigious wine estate in Northern Italy!  

I hope you like what you hear here (lol😂) please spread the word or a hundred.

John TC xx

london.name: Sonic Union
london.description:
Sweden’s Erik Pettersson is better known as S​onic Union,​ a prolific progressive house and melodic techno producer and DJ. With a DJing and production career spanning over 20 years, his versatility, experience and sheer talent enables him to turn his hand from producing, remixing and mastering to DJing and label management.

With over 200 releases to his name to date on lauded labels such as Anjunadeep, Sudbeat, Replug, Somatic and Global Underground, he has seen continued support from world class DJs such as Hernan Cattaneo, Nick Warren and Guy J. He has also remixed and been remixed by high profile artists such as Quivver, Jim Rivers, Cid Inc and Jamie Stevens to name just a few.

Erik also owns and manages well­ established label L​owbit Records,​which celebrated its milestone 150th release on 29th September 2014. With a stellar roster of artists including Cid Inc, Roland Klinkenberg, deepfunk, Guy Mantzur, Luke Porter, Marcelo Vasami, Nikko.Z, Kobana, Khen, Chicola and many more, Lowbit is renowned for its consistent championing of top quality underground dance music, and its releases are regularly supported by world class DJs including Hernan Cattaneo, John Digweed, Dave Seaman, Carl Cox, Above & Beyond and Nick Warren.

His technical prowess both behind the decks and the uniquely uplifting energy of his sets have to date seen him play in Europe, Japan, USA, Canada and India and hold residencies in his native Sweden and Canada.

https://ra.co/promoters/89871
_____________________________

Regarded as one of London’s “leading disco labels”, The Disco Express first began as a monthly loft party in March 2017; hosting the globe’s biggest house & disco DJs at the former 1940's Shoreditch railway station.

Evolving into a full-fledged record label and event series in 2020, The Disco Express is now a revered platform for nu-disco and soulful dance music. Working with the scene’s most talented up-and-coming artists, DJs and remixers, the label has established a global fanbase, distributing vinyl, merch, and music to over 50 countries worldwide. Consistent high quality releases and edits have garnered support from the likes of Nightmares On Wax, Purple Disco Machine, The Blessed Madonna, Crazy P, TSHA, Folamour, Dan Shake, Groove Armada, Sarah Story (Radio 1) and Basement Jaxx. 

Holding down residencies in London, Berlin and NYC, The Disco Express also plays host to events further afield in Milan, Rome, Trondheim and Paris. Celebrating their 50th release as a label in May 2023, The Disco Express endeavour to support new underground artists from across the globe as well as working with legends of the dance music scene Barbara Tucker, John Morales, Michael Gray, Michelle Weeks, Art of Tones and most recently Dave Lee. The Disco Express is building a strong catalogue of original disco for 21st century dance floors and this train ain't slowing down anytime soon...

london.name: Saint Etienne
london.description:
Saint Etienne are an indie dance/indie pop trio which formed in Croydon, England in 1990. The band was founded by journalist Bob Stanley (born December 25, 1964) and Pete Wiggs (born May 15, 1966) in Croydon, UK, January 1990. After recording 2 singles with guest singers, Sarah Cracknell (born April 12, 1967, Chelmsford, Essex) joined as a full member. The band is named after a French football team.

Saint Etienne are one of the bands who defined the early 90s indie dance genre, fusing the production values of the dance-pop that emerged in the wake of the Second Summer of Love with the clever lyrics and self-aware production of indie music.

london.name: Hilit Kolet
london.description:
Industry folk have deemed Hilit Kolet "the next real thing." The ascending London-based artist weaves chunky UK-tinged basslines between Chicago-influenced beats topped off with a New York sleaze-edged vibe across her productions. As a DJ, she wields multiple sound palettes from house to techno throughout her high-octane sets, mixed with razor-sharp technique. 

A classically trained musician and long-time face of Soho's legendary Black Market Records, Hilit Kolet debuted on Defected with her jackin' tune 'Techno Disco', landing at #1 on Traxsource's House chart, #1 on Music Week's Upfront Club Chart and #3 on Shazam's Discovery chart.

Support for Hilit's 100% original house cut came in strong, with Pete Tong, Danny Howard and Sarah Story rinsing 'Techno Disco' on BBC Radio 1. Since then, her production work - including her latest original single ‘POV Siren’ (Faith) and her edit of Laurent Garnier’s 90s gem 'Crispy Bacon’, which is featured on the limited edition boxset of his new album, has garnered massive support. Carl Cox, Radio Slave, Tsha, Paul Woolford, Dennis Ferrer, Patrick Topping, Eliza Rose, Nicole Moudaber, Claude Von Stroke, Hector Romero, Yousef, Mele, Heléna Star, Syreeta, La La, Emerald, HoneyLuv, Demuir, Gideön, DJ Deep, Jovonn & Tiefschwarz have all been getting behind her music, affirming Hilit Kolet as THE talent to watch.

A 360 degrees artist who defies easy classification, Hilit radiates powerful energy from the DJ booth, seducing the dancefloors of esteemed clubs Printworks, fabric, KOKO (closing after Floorplan), Warehouse Project, Ministry of Sound, Egg London and XOYO, amongst others. Snapped up by the international festival circuit, major-league gigs that Hilit has played include Lovebox, Secret Garden Party, Campo Sancho and Festival No 6. Highlights from 2022 include shows for Elrow in Croatia, Jaeger in Oslo, Ibiza, Dubai, Warsaw, and Bulgaria.

Innovative and fearless as a selector, Hilit brings her audience on an exciting ride through dance music, evoking chaos no matter the club in question. Sultry vocals, pulsating basslines and irresistible peak-time grooves spanning house, acid, techno and modern electronica feature in her sets. A forward-thinking and inimitable DJ, she shares a blend of nu-skool textures and classic moods, constantly pushing boundaries while educating her audience along the way. 

Carving out the solid yet sonically diverse path she's on today, Hilit’s roots are deeply embedded in classical music. Growing up in a musical home with a piano teacher Mum and a jazzholic Dad, Hilit had rhythm for breakfast and melodies for lunch — and played the piano before she could tie her shoelaces.

Kickstarting her journey in London, she became a key staff member of iconic vinyl retailer Black Market Records, spending every moment possible soaking up the city’s unique club culture and expanding her already encyclopedic knowledge of the scene. DJing non-stop around the capital, she built her name locally while managing a high-end recording studio where she learnt the art of music production.

With multi-dynamic studio projects and releases in the pipeline, Hilit Kolet is a rising star who, like her sound, continues to captivate. Now, she's gearing up for the next phase of an illustrious, diverse and inspiring career.

We are building up a loyal following of some of the best clubbers to ever hit club land!! Our regulars attend Shifty events for two things!!!… The Music and the Amazing Electric Atmosphere generated on our nights so intense in fact that people have gone home with a fully charged mobile phone…

london.name: K-Warren
london.description:
K-Warren was always at the forefront and pioneers of UK garage for the last 20 years with a string of radio successes to his name where he managed to take the underground into the over-ground. It has been no surprise that he made the transition to a respected producer writer of all genres with his emotive and memorable melodies in his music.

As an original member of the Architects, he was jointly responsible for the colossal remix of Brandy & Monica’s “The Boy Is Mine” and since then, K has remixed many top UK & US artists including Whitney Houston, Lil Wayne, Jay Sean, Emma Bunton, Christina Aguilera, Samantha Mumba, Shola Ama, Gabrielle, Maxi Priest & Eternal.

K teamed up with Richie Dan for the hit “Call It Fate” single and he also had has his own anthemic single “Coming Home” featuring Leo (aka Leo the Lion, vocalist from The Streets plus he recently appeared on The Voice), out on Go! Beat / Universal.

This track was a UK Top 30 hit and appeared on several TV programmes to promote it, including The Big Breakfast, Nickelodeon & Disney. K’s reproduction/remix of Ed Case’s “Something In Your Eyes” has become legendary in the garage scene and is still huge, both in the clubs and on radio.

K has co-written with other artists such as Edel’s Tymes 4 and Inferno’s Ryze and he has also remixed Lisa Stansfield, Tymes 4, MJ Cole and Bob Sinclair singles.

K has also completed a Sarah Whatmore remix for BMG, a Triple 8 remix for Polydor and has produced artist Selwyn for Sony Australia with a song he co-wrote with Phil Pickett (of Boy George – Karma Chameleon fame) for this No.1 selling artist.

He has previously had a hit single with his remix of Selwyn’s “Rich Girl” which went platinum.

More recently K has remixed Jodie Lea "Dirty Face" Jay Sean feat. Lil Wayne’s huge no.1 hit “Down”. Other songwriting / production projects include: Stacey Solomon (X-Factor/I'm A Celebrity) Paris (Fame Academy), Boy George, Shelley Nelson, Joe Killington, Blazin' Squad, Morjac, Aggro Santos, Nadia/Cherise (girls from Big Brovas / Booty Luv ), Gabriella Ellis (from Made In Chelsea), John Adeleye (aka: J’Nay) (MOBO Unsung Winner/X Factor semi finalist) and Aylin (signed to Pavarotti’s production company), Niara Scarlette (no.1 hits with Girls Aloud & Sugar Babes), Sharon Woolfe (no.1 hit Sweet Like Chocolate), Grant Black (Liberty X, Holly Valance), Curtis Richardson (J-Lo, LL Cool J, 3LW, Joss Stone)

london.description:
All enquiries: info@guymac.co.uk

An artist making continuous strides in the house and techno space with releases on Hot Creations, Black Book, Circus and more. London based DJ/Producer Guy Mac is one to watch for the future.

Inspired by leading electronic names like  Kerri Chandler, Deetron, Jamie Jones, Burnski and more, Guy’s musical inclination lends itself to the region of omniscient appreciation of all things groovy. Think deep and cadent basslines, matched with rolling percussion, soulful synth lines and more; an approach that is forward-thinking whilst tipping its hat to the very roots of electronic music.  Guy's work has found a home on some of the industry's best-known labels such as Hot Creations, Circus, Viva Music and more - garnering frequent support from a slew of the biggest names in the business. BBC Radio 1's Pete Tong and Sarah Story have been early supporters of Guy's Sonic Boom release on Hot Creations, with Pete highlighting the track on-air as a "secret weapon for Jamie Jones". Guy’s work has become commonplace in setlists of Marco Carola, Joseph Capriati, Steve Lawler, Andrea Oliva, Latmun, Hot Since 82 and countless others, heating dancefloors at Paradise, Music On, Time-warp, Space Ibiza and many more over the last half-decade.

Outside of the studio, Guy has also made a significant impact on his clubland presence. Bookings at Ministry of Sound, Egg London, ADE & Miami music week parties are just some of his notable high-lights. Often rubbing shoulders with some of his biggest inspirations, Guy has already supported the likes of Nic Fanciulli, Rossko, Solardo, Neverdogs, Pig&Dan, Yaya and Leon - among others. Guy’s relentless work ethic and continuous focus on artistic development have already left him primed for the future, keep an ear to the ground as Guy continues to elevate!

london.name: Lost Doll
london.description:
Lost Doll Presents Dream Eternal Beats (D.E.B.S) mix series in honour of Debs 

BIOG:
The small towns of Northern England raise a certain type of techno-head. When you grow up regularly spending three hours sitting on a coach just to hear the likes of Marc Smith and Scott Brown hammer it out to a sea of beetroot-face ravers at Rezerection, it shows a lot of commitment... It develops a passion, not for posing in the gauche bars of Berlin, but for letting yourself go and dancing like no-one's watching. And for Durham-born Lost Doll, that will always be the true spirit of techno.

It was the late-90s Birmingham scene that really shaped Sarah’s musical tastes. After hearing the likes of Regis, Paul Damage and, of course, the insuperable Surgeon, regularly destroy the dancefloor at House Of God, there was no turning back. And while her musical tastes have evolved, Sarah's passion and dedication to that raw, floor-focussed spirit has never changed.

Her DJ sets move from the dark, industrial and brooding through to the pounding and hypnotic, but wherever and whatever she plays, Sarah's selections are always guided by that true spirit techno - and her undying devotion to the dancefloor.

london.name: Pablo:Rita
london.description:
Pablo:Rita - DJ and vocal duo Annabel Simpson and Liz Cass have covered a huge amount of ground in a short time. The two friends started the project with their mutual love of deep house and techno and have proven to be a magnetic partnership.

2020 saw the duo achieve their first Friday Fire with Danny Howard on BBC Radio 1 with their Bontan Collaboration “Foreign Lands” on Circus Recordings which also earned them Triple J tune of the week. A string of releases followed this year on Crosstown Rebels including a track on the Spirits IV album a long with Pete Tong, Matador and Andrea Oliva, the 200th release on No Illusion with Radio 1 support from Sarah Story and a vinyl release on Rekids with remixes from Radioslave and Berghain regular Roman Fluegel.
The duo have underground releases coming on Rich NXTs imprint NXT Records and collabs with Franky Rizardo and Jansons. Separately both artists have pop/indie-dance projects and signed deals in 2021 with major labels respectively with solo singles dropping this summer. 2022 is set to be a huge year for this dynamic duo.

london.name: Sarah Lucie Shaw
london.description:
Rising UK pop-folk/country artist Sarah Lucie Shaw is currently writing and recording songs for her debut album with US producer Alan Glass (Christina Aguilera, Aretha Franklyn, Lighthouse Family). The first two tracks (demos) are the brand new song & potential single 'B Where I B'  and the co-written track  ' (The) Beginning Of Forever'  - which is already receiving publishing / sync interest. 

Sarah's original sound has influences ranging from James Morrison & Imogen Heap to Jewel & Sara Bareilles. Her debut EP was produced by Pete Hoffman at Miloco Studios (Britney Spears, Gwen Stefani) and the lead track 'I Believe In U' was picked up and signed by Silk and Denim Music, Nashville in 2011.

Sarah has graced the London singer-songwriter's scene with her engaging live set, most recently at Richard Branson's Kensington Roof Gardens*, The Bedford and the famous Troubadour venue.  She was also invited to perform at the Belfast - Nashville Songwriters Festival 2011 in Ireland.  Sarah is classically trained in both vocals & piano/keys - her powerful feminine vocal blends delicately with her strong, captivating melodies on her unique story-led songs that attain a pop sensibility throughout. 

As a songwriter, Sarah has acheived Top Ten success in the UK and accross Europe with pop/dance act Angel City, and has most recently collaborated with indie band Long-View for their forthcoming album, following on from their debut album 'Mercury' released on Warner Records UK & Sony US.

Sarah is represented worldwide by Dreamscape Global Artists Ltd.

london.name: SARAH YOUNG
london.description:
DJ/Producer Sarah Young is a multi genre artist, Dubbed by the Guardian as the 'Next Big thing'' and compared to monster producer Diplo and artist M.I.A by MTV, her music is a unique blend of sounds created for the club, influenced by international dance music.

Early Years:
Still a teenager, Sarah’s first break was playing alongside Chipmunk and Natty at a headline show in Tottenham. She has since gone on to play sets internationally at festivals and gigs at destinations such as: New York, Paris, Holland and Lithuania. During her musical journey, she has worked on a variety of projects with artists, producers and DJs such as Toddla T, RedLight, Donaeo, Mz Bratt, Mistajam, Swindle, Jammer, Roses Gabor, David HeartBreak, Lioness, Dynamite MC and J2k.


Growing up in a musical family, where international sounds filled the house, Sarah recalls her early influences, ‘’My mother was the talented musical person in the family, playing every instrument from piano, classical guitar to the flute, so I remember growing up listening to the sounds on cassette of jazz, Billie Holiday, Bob Marley, Sergio Mendez as well as classic Indian music, so Ravi Shankar was also a favourite.’’

This early exposure to music obviously influences Sarah’s DJ sets to this day, ‘When I was a teenager and started getting weekly gigs, I was djing grime, house, hiphop and reggae - all genres that a London crowd love. But once I started to get international bookings I encountered a variety of producers and Djs who played and edited variations of EDM specific to their country or city, so I became really interested in global bass, and now I play everything from Dutch House, Kuduro, Moombahton, Juke, Trap, Tropical House, Techno, Garage and anything that makes people want to dance. ‘’


Radio and Collaborations:
Sarah has been invited to play several guest mixes on BBC Asian Network and Radio 1xtra, including CJ Beatz m1x show and a VIP guest mix on DJ Kayper's show. Her continuous gig and radio exposure has led to partnerships with high profile brands such as Redbull, Adidas, MTV, WeSC and Westfield Stratford on various projects from CD releases to writing music columns and DJ-ing at store opening parties.

Sarah Debuted a guest dance show on the famous Ministry of Sound radio on 12th March 2013 featuring world exclusives and interviews from Sway, Ryan Babel and a mini guest mix by Slick Shoota.

Production:
When she’s not spinning, Sarah is in her studio working on a continuous roll of new music releases. She’s already released an EP with Adidas Originals entitled ‘i am Sarah Young’ and a mix CD with WeSC called ‘Moombahton Queen’. Following the success of these collaborations, Sarah followed this up with her highly anticipated second solo 3-track EP  Autumn 2012. Retaining elements of her Global Bass roots, the new EP has a bouncier BMP exploring Hip Hop, early 90’s Acid House, Trap, Garage and subsequent EDM genres with guest MCs from across the Atlantic. The EP aimed to make a Global Bass hybrid more relevant to a UK & US audience.

Currently Sarah is working on a brand new album project.

london.name: sarah-violin
london.description:
Sarahviolin (Mallock) is a professional musician and violinist. Electric violinist Sarah creates a new twist with a cutting-edge sound, combining sound effects and modern technology to provide a sensational atmosphere. Her repertoire includes Groove Armada, Jose Padilla, the Gotan Project and many well know and remixed Deep House grooves and Electro tracks.

Sarah’s media performances include live on Jules Holland, Parkinson, Jonathan Ross and Jo Whiley on Radio 2 as well as appearing more than 50 times on Top of The Pops, plus pretty much every other show on TV that have live music on, The National Lottery. During the past 12 years, Sarah has performed for a diverse range of artists and luxury brands and has extensively toured Europe and the UK. In 2012 she was invited to perform as part of an ofﬁcial performance for the 2012 London Olympics, Team GB closing party – a truly unforgettable experience. Brands she has performed for include Moet Hennessy, Relais Chateaux and Aston Martin. Sarah has appeared at V Festival, Glastonbury, and Latitude and many more festivals.

london.name: sarahjohnsmusicparty
london.description:
Sarah Johns Music Party is from the North of England and now lives in London. Her stripped back, organic, drum, guitar and vocals, give her work an immediate and honest feel that is at once comforting and yet unnerving. Her music recalls the purity of Lykki Li, the rawness of Scout Niblett and the musicality of Tune-Yards. 

Sarah Johns is influenced by nature, with much of her work echoing the repetition of 19th Century American black and white Christian Spiritual Song. Sarah Johns Music Party’s live performance continues this likeness by exploring the therapeutic and meditative effect of music upon the audience, mindful of the ritual of people coming together to listen to and play music.

Inspirations: Stop Making Sense (The Talking Heads live video), 808 drum machines, Hermann Hesse, Samba, cheerleaders, ceremonies, games with rules, the bit where it all comes together in jazz and the bit before and after, Oh Lord Won’t You Buy Me a Mercedes Benz, Salt-N-Pepa, Laurie Anderson.

Sarah Johns has previously recorded an art folk record with Max Jung under the name Cool Fun. The video to their track, House, won seven awards including Best Pop Video (Budget) at the UK Music Video Awards, Best Music Video at The European Independent Film Festival and Best Music Short at the London Short Film Festival. Sarah Johns was also one half of Mr Beasley, an electronic duo who toured with Robyn and whose album How Do You Say? spawned three singles: Right As Rain, Neon and Wrong which collectively achieved a ‘Single of the Week’ on BBC 6Music (Nemone’s lunchtime show),  Best Unsigned on Huw Stephens’ BBC Radio 1 show and plays on XFM and NME radio. Sarah Johns Music Party EP will be Sarah Johns’ debut release as Sarah Johns Music Party, released on 8th July on brand new label Psychic Healing Network, founded by members of London band MYSTYRYS.

After recently winning Battersea Arts Centre’s Jim Marcovitch Award, Sarah Johns is currently working on a piece merging performance art and music and will be performing at Battersea Arts Centre on 12th June, with another project being planned for The Yard Theatre, Hackney Wick (14th – 18th May).

london.name: K-Warren
london.description:
K-Warren was always at the forefront and pioneers of UK garage for the last 20 years with a string of radio successes to his name where he managed to take the underground into the over-ground. It has been no surprise that he made the transition to a respected producer writer of all genres with his emotive and memorable melodies in his music.

As an original member of the Architects, he was jointly responsible for the colossal remix of Brandy & Monica’s “The Boy Is Mine” and since then, K has remixed many top UK & US artists including Whitney Houston, Lil Wayne, Jay Sean, Emma Bunton, Christina Aguilera, Samantha Mumba, Shola Ama, Gabrielle, Maxi Priest & Eternal.

K teamed up with Richie Dan for the hit “Call It Fate” single and he also had has his own anthemic single “Coming Home” featuring Leo (aka Leo the Lion, vocalist from The Streets plus he recently appeared on The Voice), out on Go! Beat / Universal.

This track was a UK Top 30 hit and appeared on several TV programmes to promote it, including The Big Breakfast, Nickelodeon & Disney. K’s reproduction/remix of Ed Case’s “Something In Your Eyes” has become legendary in the garage scene and is still huge, both in the clubs and on radio.

K has co-written with other artists such as Edel’s Tymes 4 and Inferno’s Ryze and he has also remixed Lisa Stansfield, Tymes 4, MJ Cole and Bob Sinclair singles.

K has also completed a Sarah Whatmore remix for BMG, a Triple 8 remix for Polydor and has produced artist Selwyn for Sony Australia with a song he co-wrote with Phil Pickett (of Boy George – Karma Chameleon fame) for this No.1 selling artist.

He has previously had a hit single with his remix of Selwyn’s “Rich Girl” which went platinum.

More recently K has remixed Jodie Lea "Dirty Face" Jay Sean feat. Lil Wayne’s huge no.1 hit “Down”. Other songwriting / production projects include: Stacey Solomon (X-Factor/I'm A Celebrity) Paris (Fame Academy), Boy George, Shelley Nelson, Joe Killington, Blazin' Squad, Morjac, Aggro Santos, Nadia/Cherise (girls from Big Brovas / Booty Luv ), Gabriella Ellis (from Made In Chelsea), John Adeleye (aka: J’Nay) (MOBO Unsung Winner/X Factor semi finalist) and Aylin (signed to Pavarotti’s production company), Niara Scarlette (no.1 hits with Girls Aloud & Sugar Babes), Sharon Woolfe (no.1 hit Sweet Like Chocolate), Grant Black (Liberty X, Holly Valance), Curtis Richardson (J-Lo, LL Cool J, 3LW, Joss Stone)

london.name: Emma and The Sound
london.description:
Bill Curbishly manager of The Who is a fan of Emma and The Sound. We are quite chuffed! Emma is frequently referenced as the new current kate bush for her artist approach to songs like a short film in a song or work on canvas as she likes to describe it! 

SUPPORTING CHRIS SLADE AC/DC SEPTEMBER 20TH AT THE UNDERWORLD IN CAmden

Emma is a stylised cinematic alternative rock singer-songwriter, fresh on the music scene with her current band and distinctive unique sound. Named the current mFrequently referenced as the current kate Bush. A storyteller connecting to her audience touching on themes of tragic romance, politics, human desire with a twist of surrealism. She is becoming well known for her alluring bittersweet melancholy fusion. She textures her work with progressive clever rock riffs merged with a delicate acoustic. Her love for strings and classical influences are infused into her sound. For Emma writing music is like sculpting a piece of art. She is honest, fearless and provocative in her stories and truth. Emma wears her heart on her sleeve and writes based on her emotions and life experiences revealing herself at her best and worse as an open book.

She has performed for the Cirque Du Soleil private party in Ibiza and performed alongside PP Arnold, Chris Farlow, Ronnie Wood, Mark Joseph.

 She is also an actress and drama school graduate recently acting in 2 feature films. She's a poet, surreal artist/painter of female nudes that mirror her poetical song writing. She is a multifaceted artist who's various media all merge and inspire the other. She sees them as one. She dreams melody's and lyrics with a dictaphone always by her bed... as you do! 

'songs are a canvas' Emma

THE SOUND are her band Don on guitar, Mike drums, Jules on bass guitar. 

She is the daughter of Jimmy Winston from the 60's band 'The Small Faces'. 

Emma's an animal rights warrior! Lets protect and treat our animal friends better! www.soidog.org (please extend your support to these truly amazing human beings)'

'With success comes huge responsibility...use it well to make positive changes for a better world. Use any power gifted to you not for self gain but to help others believe in their dreams and never give up on them. Hold in there! Music is an international language that can break down barriers and plug into everyones emotions. There's no greater dream for me than to be a voice for my animals pals too.' Emma

BRAND SUPPORT Michael Kors, Amanda Wakeley and GIGI Vintage for dressing me.
Phtotgrapher Anna Marchesani.

london.name: Emma Hatton
london.description:
From her recent International residency as guest vocalist for the world renowned Post Modern Jukebox back to her earliest forays into jazz and blues, Emma’s impact upon the music scene is undeniable.  


Influenced and inspired by legends of song Eva Cassidy, Sarah Vaughan, Etta Jamesand Carole King among many more, Emma’s origins have left her as comfortable singing blues as she is soul, jazz and country. What defines her is that she resists being defined – her versatility creating demand for Emma worldwide as a solo artist.  
 
Following the release of her critically acclaimed debut EP with Anthony Strong, which went straight to Number 1 on the iTunes Jazz and Blues chart, Emma has sold out solo shows across the UK.
​
Equally at home in front of thousands as she is in an intimate setting, Emma is a much sought after vocalist and has provided lead vocals for numerous film and television projects, such as Finding Your Feet, the Marvel series and NBC Universal.
 
Emma’s soaring voice and transformative abilities as a performer mean she has also amassed a huge fan base in the world of stage, having starred in the West End as Eva Peron in Evita, Elphaba in Wicked and Scaramouche in We Will Rock You.
 
The remainder of 2018 will see Emma release her second independent EP on vinyl, arranged by and featuring Anthony Strong together with British Jazz Award winner Freddie Gavita on trumpet.

London-based female artist EmCave is pushing the genre barriers - Vintage Pop with Trip-Hop undertones fused with fresh Indie music.
Singer-songwriter Emma Arden interweaves powerful melodies with vividly evocative lyrics drawn from personal experience in order to share her stories.
 
Early operatic training enables Emma to bring a range, depth and timbre to her work that couldn’t be more different today in tone and approach. Her influences are wide and include Jill Scott, Portishead and the Cocteau Twins.

Emma says “After singing classically for so long, I reached a point where I wanted to explore a new kind of music. It’s so exciting to develop different ways of working at a deeper emotional level, which I hope will resonate with my audience.”

london.name: EMMA ROBIN MUSIC 🫦
london.description:
Emma Robin, a captivating singer-songwriter hailing from the Netherlands, has been enchanting listeners with her soulful blend of pop, R&B, and jazz influences since relocating to London in 2018 to pursue her dream of becoming a professional recording artist. Driven by her passion for music and a desire to make her mark, Emma's distinctive sound channels the essence of iconic artists like Adele, Amy Winehouse, India Arie, and Stevie Wonder.

From a tender age, Emma was captivated by the rich, evocative sounds of jazz and soul legends like Ella Fitzgerald, Stevie Wonder, and Aretha Franklin. These early influences ignited her love for music and shaped her unique vocal style. As she embarked on her musical journey in London, Emma began collaborating with acclaimed songwriters such as James Essien (Clean Bandit) and Jonny Rockstar (Amy Winehouse), creating a fusion of pop, soul, and R&B that resonates with today's contemporary music scene.

Inspired by the raw, heartfelt lyricism of Amy Winehouse and the emotive power of Adele's voice, Emma's music is infused with authenticity and vulnerability. She possesses a remarkable ability to tackle serious subjects with a lighthearted, humorous twist, making her songs both relatable and engaging.

Her upcoming single, "Good Times," delves into the complexities of living a seemingly perfect life while grappling with internal struggles. The track explores the notion that money can't buy happiness, and that wealth can sometimes be a mere temporary distraction from the emotional battles one faces in their day-to-day life.

As Emma Robin continues to expand her musical horizons and refine her signature sound, she is undoubtedly an artist to watch in the pop, soul, and R&B landscapes. With her enchanting voice, thought-provoking lyrics, and a growing repertoire of captivating tracks, Emma is poised to become a prominent figure in today's music scene. Keep an ear out for this rising star and her compelling, genre-defying tunes.

It consist's of 10 Deep Soulful Vocal House trax that are smooth sounding, and send out a deep spiritual uplifting message!!    

Emma May’s passion for music has been clear from the beginning. She began performing in several church choirs and musical theatre productions from a very young age. Emma May trained at The Brit School of Performing arts and Technology; her peers included Leona Lewis and Amy Winehouse. This valuable experience led her to work with various industry professionals in the US and UK including Lionel and Trevor Job (Tyrese), Pete Hammond (Kylie Minogue, Alpha Beat) and Kim Glover (Aretha Franklin, Whitney Houston)
Emma May is a key member of the CK Gospel Choir. This unique Multi vocalist group have toured the UK and Europe and performed with top artists such as Peter Andre, Beverley Knight, The Feeling, Josh Groban and jamie Cullum to name a few. Her work as a backing vocalist includes the hit ITV show XFactor and a UK tour with Simon Clothier supporting The Soldiers.

london.name: ArtistSethGuy
london.description:
These recordings were made for Emma McNally's blog during the MIRRORCITY exhibition at The Hayward Gallery 14th October 2014 until 4th January 2015. Emma McNally posted regularly to the Southbank Centre blog using text, image and sound to explore and expand upon the themes of her work featured in the exhibition.

Invited by McNally to contribute audio to this blog, I made several recordings gathered on walks at various locations in close proximity to Emma McNally's studio situated at the West India Dock. The site of her studio and its relationship to networks of water, commerce and communication is reflected in her large-scale drawings. Using a combination of archival and contemporary documents McNally made a complex and evolving portrait of an area of the city rich in cultural, economic and military history.

This project is now complete but is archived on the Southbank Centre's website. For more information and material by Seth Guy and to view the blog please use the links below.

london.name: deanfacer
london.description:
Professional DJ since 1987, now internationally acclaimed DJ, producer, remixer, promoter, radio DJ, label owner, artist manager and record reviewer for OurHouse magazine, IDM magazine and Resident Advisor.

Underground music has always been a passion for Dean Facer, initially when he was a teenager Dean would immerse himself in the soul, jazz funk and hip hop scenes via the early pirates radio stations such as Jazz FM, Solar and of course when Kiss FM was still a pirate station and then when the early house sounds starting filtering over to the UK from Chicago and New York, Dean then knew that music was his calling in life.

Dean started to DJ back in 1987, after a few years playing in London and surrounding areas he started to build up his reputation for superb mixing and excellent track selection. In 1994 he started to play the harder side of house music and quickly became a very successful Hard House DJ throughout the UK and Europe, and now plays all around the world. In 2004 he changed the style that he plays and he now concentrates on the pure underground side of House music and showing his versatility he plays everything from sultry jazzy vibes and deep house to full on tribal and tech house, minimal and techno depending on the night / festival he has been booked for and with his passion for discovering unknown artists and tracks from across the globe his sets are always fresh and exhilarating.

Dean has also promoted some of his own nights that have proved to be very successful. Nights such as the legendary “United Colors Of House” which began back in 1994 and has been re-launched as a weekly club night. Also, Syvässä a night of the best sultry deep house, and the cheekily named “Bash Yer Bishop!” as well as earlier success' with “Slamm” and “Pure House” (Co-promoted with DJ Magazine / DMC's Lewis Dene).

Radio is another area that Dean has been involved with frequently, both local and national. Dean used to do regular guest slots on “Saturday Late”- CRMK 89:8 FM and then went on to host the hugely popular "United Colors Of House" show on CRMK 89:8FM on Sunday evenings between 19:00-22:00 hrs (UK time) which is streamed on the United Colors Of House website, as well as this he guests on national stations such as Germany’s Kiss FM, Hungary’s FM Czéski, Norway's Radio Pluss, Italy's Klubb 105, Holland's Club Madnezz and Switzerland’s Radio 24. 

The success of the United Colors Of House show can be seen with list of the world’s elite DJ’s that had submitted guest mixes for the last hour of the show including the likes of DJ Sneak, Sven Väth, Wally Lopez, David Duriez, Trentmøller, Josh Wink, David Guetta, Kerri Chandler, Sonny Wharton, Deepgroove, Quentin Harris, Darren Emerson through to legends of the underground house and techno scenes such as Anja Schneider, Slok, m_ferri, Dave Slide, Re-Zone, Shonky, Dan Ghenacia, Guy Gerber, David Gausa, Modunique, M.A.N.D.Y., and Jussi-Pekka Parrika

Dean has now passed the reigns of the weekly United Colors Of House over to his co-host Oz, who continues to the show in the same format every Sunday evening between 19:00-22:00hrs and Oz is now joined by Adam J, although Dean does intend getting back in the radio studio for a new weekly show very soon.

Also recently set up is Dean’s new label, Veena Recordings, which of course will feature tracks from Dean himself as well as tracks signed from all over the world and covering all quality styles of underground house and techno.

As well as his DJing, Dean is now also a well-respected producer and remixer, gaining support from the worlds leading DJ’s with releases and remixes out on labels such as: 
Absolutely Records (Italy),
Öften Grüven (Canada), 
Moonbeam Tribal (Russia), 
Helvetica Noir (Switzerland), 
Tidy Trax (UK), 
Action (UK), 
Dial-Emma (UK),
Meaty Moosic (UK) 
and the hugely successful white label series called “FAT”.   

“Waitin” FAT 002 (The Guinness ad) this was reviewed in Mixmag & given the 4 dancing men, as well as Lisa Lashes saying that it was her favourite remix of all time.

“Boys Like U” reviewed in Muzik by Mark Kavanagh & NCM by Sarah G, and was signed to the Tidy Trax compilation album “The Annual” that was released in May 2001, and gained huge support from the likes of Fergie, 
The Tidy Boys, Nick Rafferty and the rest of the Hard House elite.

“Fun & Games” reviewed in Wax by Johnny Dangerous who gave it 7/10. 

“Just Because…” this was signed up for the Tidy Trax compilation as well as “Boys Like U”. It was also reviewed in DJ by Simon Eve and played on Radio 1 by the late John Peel.

“Re:-Born” FAT 003 is the track that has created a massive buzz on both sides of the Atlantic. The Tidy Boys said that this was their biggest record on their ‘01 tour of USA, and also had Judge Jules rushing back to the stage to ask Rob Tissera about the track at Gatecrasher’s Summer Soundstage and support from DJ’s worldwide and was highly placed in the “Hype Chart” in 
DJ Magazine.

“What The Funk” Gained huge response everywhere, and signed to Dial-Emma records. Also included on the Insomnia 2 compilation CD released in March 2002, mixed by the Stimulant DJ’s and supported by everyone from Fergie, The Tidy Trax, Sarah G, Lisa Lashes, Anne Savage etc.

“Honey, I Drugged The Kids” Released on Hard Trax and huge everywhere including Anne Savage charting it as one of her biggest tracks in Ibiza 2002 as well as John Peel opening his Radio 1 show with it on 10/7/02.

“Playin’ With Fire” Big in the hands of Rob Tissera, Anne Savage, Andy Farley, BK, Ed Real, Charlotte Birch and Lee Haslam. 

Dean gained huge support for his Hard House tracks from DJ's such as Lisa Lashes, Anne Savage, Fergie, The Tidy Boys, Sarah G, Rob Tissera, Andy Farley and the legendry John Peel etc. 

First release on Veena Recordings was a 3am style dark dubby tech-house number titled "United" and is already getting big support from the likes of Sonny Wharton, Hernan Cattaneo, Chlöe Harris, Kenny Wee, Sharam Jey, DJ Shield, Linus,  Afroboogie, Piliavin and Zimbardo, Stama, and a select few others, and made a high entry in the DJ Magazine Hype Chart. Released in Feb 2006 and jumped into the top 20 of the DJ Magazine “Hype Chart”. “United” has now been signed for a full worldwide release on the London based, Axis Records for release in early 2009.

Dean Facer's 3am Mix of the latest track from Moonbeam feat: Amigo "Basic Instinct" on the Russian label, Moonbeam Tribal Records, due out at the end September and already supported & played by Sonny Wharton, Hernan Cattaneo, Deepgroove, Yves Eaux, Pete Tong, Sam Ball, Stama (Erase Records, Greece), Linus (Exun Records, Germany) etc and was released in September 2006.

Next came an anthem of a remix on BP Zulauf’s label, Helvetica Noir, the track called “Far West” by DJ Kramer & Mike Gianani and was a driving tech house monster and a firm favourite with most of the worlds foremost tastemaking DJ’s including Chus & Cabellos, Kenny Wee, Sharam Jey, DJ Kramer & Mike Gianani and of course the label boss, Bp Zulauf himself.

Then came a remix that Dean did for one of his favourite labels, Öften Grüven Records based in Montreal, Canada. It’s a track by Electric Circus called “Blackboard”. The remix was finished in early May 2008 and was released in November 2008. Big support came from DJ’s such as Fred Numf, Q-Burns,
Kenny Wee, Deepgroove, Sonny Wharton, Phunk Investigation, Chlöe Harris, Pete Tong, Dan de Leon,
Oz, Jalebee Cartel and Christian Paduraru to name a few.

Following on from this was a remix for a label that Dean has supported for many years, the Moscow based, Underground Systems. The remix was for the DJ / producer from Belarus, namely, Igor Shep.
His EP called “Moon” is a great slice of tech-house and Dean’s mix give it a nice “old school” vibe that gained support from DJ’s: Rulers Of The Deep, Henri Köhn, Reza, Phil Hooton, Q-Burns, Fred Numf and Full Body Sound System’s Damon G.

Most recently Dean was commissioned to do a remix for the legendary Italian duo, Phunk Investigation, on their remake of Joe Smooth’s all time House anthem, “The Promised Land”. The original mix was launched at the Amsterdam Dance Event 2008, with the remix from Dean now complete and support for the remix coming in from the DJ elite such as; Bob Sinclar, Paul van Dyk, Judge Jules, Eddie Amador, Hector Romero, Danny Rampling, Chus, Johan Gielen, Robert Graf, Tom Schaffer (Beatport), Alan Thompson, Flash Brothers, Pete Gooding, Dave Lambrechts, Bogdan Taran, Sharp & Smooth, Lewis Dene, Sonny Wharton, Kenny Wee, Lys, Oz, Jalebee Cartel, Sakke Haaranen (House amigo’s), Stonemason, Anne Savage, Reza, Jonathan Ulysses, Lenny Fontana, Re-Zone, Alex Flatner etc.

Hailed as 'Jessie J meets Joan Jett' FRANSIS (formally known as Emma & the Idles) are an indie rock band based in London, U.K. made up of front woman and singer songwriter Emma Withers, guitarists Alex Scott, Stefan Kotlarz and bassist Craig Rattray. With a balls to the wall approach to their sound and sharp songwriting style, they have regularly been compared to the likes of Wolf Alice and Florence + the machine. Each song will smack you in the face in a slightly different way, and whilst they float between genres of rock, indie, pop, soul and blues; they show an unrelenting penchant for dramatic, powerful and meaningful music. 

With a fresh rebrand and new music on the horizon, 2022 will be a significant and exciting year for these guys. Stay tuned…

london.name: The Mariner's Children
london.description:
Established in Brighton after a chance meeting in Vietnam, The Mariner’s Children are an English alternative folk band, consisting of Benedict Rubinstein (vocals, guitar, banjo), Daniel Matthews (guitar, banjo, mandolin), Emma Gatrill (vocals, accordion, glockenspiel), Marcus Hamblett (bass, banjo), Emma Kraemer (violin), Becca Mears (cello), and Felix Weldon (drums). With colliding guitar duels and soaring strings, The Mariner's Children make a type of music that is cinematic, pastoral, and entirely their own. Described by The Guardian as creators of something with "the visceral attack of rock and the rhythmic propulsion and thrilling momentum of dance", their songs build from the sparse, delicate understatement of the likes of Iron & Wine and Pentangle into huge, encompassing Arcade Fire-like walls of sound, providing the perfect foil to the troubled romanticism of Rubinstein's lyrics. As an ensemble of multi-instrumentalists, they have formerly lent their individual talents to such acts as Laura Marling, Alessi's Ark, Broken Social Scene, and Peggy Sue, but the group are now poised to make their collective mark with their own project.

Whilst this year has already seen them tour the UK and Ireland extensively with American troubadour Willy Mason, the band will be hitting the road again in November with Bear's Den (Communion) fresh off their breakout US tour. Following on from two critically-acclaimed EPs, early 2014 will see the release of The Mariner's Children's much-anticipated debut album, "Over My Body, Roses They Rise". Shortly thereafter, the band is set to embark on their inaugural North American tour.

"The Mariner's Children roar with the hot-headed intensity of Arcade Fire, made brittle with tumultuous rage and regret."
- NME

"Simply astonishing...exhilarating and devastating...a thrilling journey."
- Q Magazine

"Sets an impossibly high level of expectations of any future endeavors...an intimate, poignant release that's impressive in every way."
- The Line Of Best Fit

london.name: Q and A
london.description:
Q and A are a four-piece, London based band comprising Emma James, Rory Thomas, Joe Wheeler and Johno Donacchie. The band formed in 2012, motivated by a common desire to create an exciting, innovative and unique brand of guitar-driven music fusing an unusual combination of musical influences from a wide range of sources.

The band has aimed to avoid falling into genre convention, instead choosing to incorporate elements from apparently disparate artists and genres, from Michael Jackson to Sonic Youth, free jazz to drum and bass. 

The foundation of their sound is Joe and Johno’s rhythm section. Melodic bass lines, underlined by aggressive, cyclical drumming provide a backdrop to Rory’s intense, thrashing guitar playing and richly textured, powerful vocals, and new addition Emma provides a ghostly, smoky, soulful vocal counterpoint to the band’s sound. Rory’s lyrics are often cryptic, sometimes surreal and flavoured by a dose of black humour. Often featuring recurring characters, the lyrics provide the script to the band’s cinematic musical design.

Currently the band is self-producing an upcoming four track EP, due for release in September. You can hear some of the band’s demo quality tracks on Soundcloud at soundcloud.com/qandaband. For more information, please find them on Facebook, Twitter, Tumblr or email them at qandaband@london.com.

‘Dead Boyfriend E.P.’ available September, date TBC.


For Bookings & Press Contact:

qandaband@london.com
