london.name: Colleen Cosmo Murphy
london.description:
Colleen ‘Cosmo’ Murphy is a highly respected and experienced musical selector, DJ, radio host and curator, founder of the album listening event and content hub Classic Album Sundays and an authority on music, sound and the vinyl renaissance.
 
She was mentored by David Mancuso at his seminal Loft parties in New York City. Together they co-produced the compilation series David Mancuso Presents The Loft and worked together on David’s record label The Loft Audiophile Library of Music. In 2000, David told Time Out New York City “She is very devoted and very pure about the music. She’s one of the only people I would trust, both with the music and with the equipment, to fill in for me.” She was asked by David to help manage his legacy and continues to be one of the musical hosts at The Loft in NYC. She is also the co-founder of the Lucky Cloud Loft parties in London and DJs internationally on the world's best sound systems and dance floors.

Colleen hosts Cosmodelica, a monthly radio show on Worldwide FM selected by Time Out as one of the 10 best shows in London. She is now bringing Cosmodelica to the dancefloor to high-end audio venues like London’s Giant Steps and New York City’s Public Records. In March she is hosting a Cosmodelica residency at the Prince of Wales with special guests.

In 2019 Colleen was nominated into the DJ Mag North America Hall of Fame and launched Love Dancin’ Sound System at Gilles Peterson’s We Out Here Festival, sharing some of her musical and sonic passions to dancers outside of her existing communities to rave reviews. She will once again host the Love Dancin’ tent at We Out Here in 2020.

In the last few years Colleen has brought her uplifting musical energy to other festivals including Houghton where she has hosted a marathon set every year since its inception and is returning in 2020. She has played alongside Gilles Peterson for his closing party at his Worldwide Festival, a headline closing set at Dekmantel Selectors 2019 and sets at Kala Festival, Lost Village, One Day at the Disco, Flow Festival and Umbria Jazz Festival.

She hosted one of the most popular disco sets for Boiler Room and has recently been featured as the subject of a podcast for Resident Advisor. DJ Mag UK featured a lengthy long-read article about her in August 2019.

 Her Classic Album Sundays platform tells the stories behind the albums that have shaped our culture and in some cases, our lives. Colleen founded Classic Album Sundays as a stance against the increasing devaluation of music and sound. What began as a passion project is now the world’s most popular album listening event with satellites in four continents and the website and social media channels host content on classic albums and artists such as interviews, videos, playlists and more. BBC Breakfast Television remarked, “Classic Album Sundays treat our best-loved records like great symphonies.” She has hosted events with amazing talent such as Jarvis Cocker, Guy Garvey, Laura Mvula, Max Richter, John Grant, Pink Floyd’s Nick Mason and many more.
 
Colleen has been a radio host, DJ and programme director since the age of fourteen and today hosts Cosmodelica and Classic Album Sundays Worldwide on Worldwide FM and ‘This Women’s Work’ series for Public Radio International. She is the writer and host of BBC 6 Music’s album series ‘Sounds of a City’ and BBC Radio 4’s doc series ‘Turntable Tales’. Unfold Japan, a radio series she hosted for Worldwide FM and Asahi, has recently been nominated for an ARIA Award (Audio and Radio Industry Awards).

london.name: Anna Meredith
london.description:
Anna Meredith is a composer, producer and performer of both acoustic and electronic music.  Her sound is frequently described as ‘maximalist’ ‘uncategorisable’ and ‘genre-hopping’ and straddles the different worlds of contemporary classical, avant pop, electronica and experimental rock. 

Her music has been performed everywhere from the BBC Last Night of the Proms to flashmob body-percussion performances in the M6 Services, PRADA fashion campaigns, numerous films, installations and documentaries, pop festivals, clubs and classical concert halls worldwide and broadcast on Radio 1, 2, 3, 4 & 6.

She has been Composer in Residence with the BBC Scottish Symphony Orchestra, RPS/PRS Composer in the House with Sinfonia ViVA, the classical music representative for the 2009 South Bank Show Breakthrough Award and winner of the 2010 Paul Hamlyn Award for Composers.

Her recent piece Connect It was written for the BBC’s award winning Ten Pieces scheme which involved half of all UK Primary school children working on Connect It as well as Anna leading broadcasts, workshops and performances including at Radio 2’s Proms in the Park to 40,000 people.

 Anna's two EPs - Black Prince Fury and Jet Black Raider were released on Moshi Moshi Records to critical acclaim including Drowned in Sound's Single of the Year.

She performs with her band of classical musicians and a line up of Anna on clarinet and electronics plus two cellists, electric guitar, tuba and drums.  They have performed everywhere from Latitude to Ether festivals, la Gaîté Lyrique, Le Guess Who to classical music festivals and residencies.  

Recent projects have included collaborations with Laura Marling and The Stranglers for the first 6Music Prom, commissions for the Aurora Orchestra, Scottish Ensemble, Netherlands Chamber Orchestra and Living Earth Duo, Installations for Sleep-Pods in Singapore and Park Benches in Hong Kong and the world's first Concerto for Beatboxer and Orchestra.

Anna's debut album Varmints was released on Moshi Moshi/PIAS 6th March 2016

london.description: THE GREENERS are a London and Bristol based trio (and sometimes more), who use multiple acoustic instruments and intricate vocal harmonies to create their innovative sound. Their roots are in folk/pop/bluegrass, featuring deadpan, satirical lyrics, setting black comedy about the world around them to ear-worm riffs and soaring melodies. Drawing influence from seminal artists such as Fleetwood Mac, Laura Marling, Elbow and The The, their sound has been compared to Tom Waits, Fleet Foxes and Nickel Creek. london.name: julianlennon
london.description:
Julian Lennon’s sensitive and poetic vision of life courses through his acclaimed music. On June 4th he returns with his first album in 15 years, the stunning Everything Changes (Music From Another Room), a masterwork of powerfully vulnerable and sophisticatedly accessible adult pop. 

Julian’s melding of uplifting introspection and thoughtful social commentary with refined hooks has made for a compelling six-album body of work. His debut, Valotte (Atlantic), yielded two top ten hits—the title track and "Too Late for Goodbyes”—and was nominated for a Grammy for “Best New Artist.” He went on to have #1 singles on the U.S. album rock charts. Internationally, one of his most popular songs “Saltwater” charted successfully around the world, topping in Australia for four weeks and reached #6 in the UK. In advance of its June 4th U.S. release, his latest, Everything Changes (Music From Another Room), is already receiving national airplay and press plaudits nationally and internationally.  The Sunday Press calls it a “revelation” and Herald Standard gushes Julian has “returned stronger and better than ever.” 

Everything Changes is a stunning achievement. It’s stately and intimate, and thoughtfully paced. Lyrically, it covers romance, introspection, and humanitarian concerns with artistic concision, mixing clever wordplay with emotional directness. The poignancy and poise of “Everything Changes” opens the album and sets a universally spiritual tone. The beautifully crafted lead off single “Someday” features mystical Eastern melodic motifs and boasts guest vocalist Steven Tyler. It engagingly combines Julian’s lifework as a philanthropist and gifted songwriter. Here, Julian sings pristinely with earnestness the timeless message: “We’re all in it together / One love, now and forever.” Other album standouts are the mesmerizing piano pop ballad "Lookin' 4 Luv" and the euphoric rocker “Just For You.”

Besides Steven Tyler, also guesting on the album is musician/producer Peter Vettese (Jethro Tull, Annie Lennox, Pet Shop Boys), singer-songwriter Paul Buchanan (Blue Nile), legendary songwriter Mark Spiro (Heart, Laura Branigan, Lita Ford), singer/producer/composer Tim Ellis, as well as longtime friends Gregory Darling, Justin Clayton, and Guy Pratt. Julian and Grant Ransom jointly produced the album. 

Everything Changes has all the hallmarks of Julian Lennon’s classic, sublime lifestyle music, yet glows with tender wisdom gleaned from his many life explorations.

DOLORES's music is not limited by one genre or category.  This is DOLORES music; songs that centre around emotional distress, uneasy relationships, personal trauma and myriad life experiences.

DOLORES's voice and songs have been described as: unique, original, imaginative and daring, elegant and expressive, atmospheric, melancholic, beguiling, haunting, rich in tone, emotive

london.name: Laura Piras
london.description:
Laura Piras (B.A. (Hons) MMus, MA) specialises in the performance of 17th, 18th & 19th century works on historical flutes. She studied for a M.A. in Historical Performance at the Royal Academy of Music with Lisa Beznosiuk and Rachel Brown, graduating with Distinction and winning the prestigious Nancy Nuttall Early Music Prize.

Laura has performed with The Hanover Band, Parley of Instruments, London Baroque Sinfonia, Little Baroque Company, London Handel Orchestra, Southern Sinfonia, International Baroque Soloists, Arcangelo and Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment for education projects and as part of the Ann & Peter Law Experience.

Laura has performed in concerts directed by Sir Mark Elder, Jeffrey Skidmore and Laurence Cummings and regularly as a soloist in the RAM/Kohn Bach Cantata Series directed by Iain Ledingham, including a concert directed by John Butt. Laura also performs with baroque chamber ensemble The Regent’s Soloists.

Before specialising in historical performance Laura read music at the University of East Anglia, receiving a B.A. (Hons) and a M.Mus on modern flute. She was awarded four major scholarships for performance studies from the School of Music (Hilda Houssart, Britten-Pears, Imogen Holst and Frank Thistlethwaite scholarships) which enabled her to receive flute lessons from William Sleath and Paul-Edmund Davies. On graduating she was awarded the Dorothea and Rowan Hare Young Musicians Concert, a prize awarded to one UEA music graduate per year.

Laura is also an enthusiastic and dedicated flute teacher to adults and children. She teaches in London and her experience includes a post as flute teacher for the University of East Anglia from 2007-11. She currently teaches at Graveney School in Tooting.

london.name: Leftroom
london.description:
Leftroom Records opened its doors in August of 2005 in Nottingham, England. The label is the creation of Matt Tolfrey (Owner). Musically, it was one of the first labels of its kind in the UK, showcasing the off centre sound of house, disco and techno.

Distributed now by Above Board, the first release surfaced for the label on the 5th of December 2005 and was entitled ‘The Extended Family EP’ encapsulating the spirit of Leftroom, a place where a core set of artists could grow and experiment with their sound. The Leftroom family consists of a few key artists including Laura Jones, Huxley, Gavin Herlihy, Sam Russo and Matt himself.

April 2006 saw the launch of Leftroom's sublabel, Leftroom Limited. Musically Leftroom Limited brings a new dimension to Leftroom as a whole, concentrating on anything that wobbles from straight up house, to techno and even the uplifting. The first ep for the sublabel was Tolfrey & Sylvester presents: Popeye-Spinach Disko, a slow brewing, techy, disco record, which came out the end of May 06 with many plaudits. 

With Matt being label owner he proved his A&R capabilities are pin-point in securing one of 2007’s biggest tracks, Ito & Star’s ‘Suduko Kid’ and one of 2008’s biggest crossover tracks, Rocha and Lewinger’s ‘Down Seq’. The summer of 2011 brought you Laura Jones's 'Love In Me' which was a global phenomenon, and Maceo Plex's remix of the same track was Leftroom's first no 1 overall seller on Beatport. In 2012 Kate Simko's 'Go On Then' featuring Jem Cooke stole all headlines, and the same year brought you Matt's debut artist album 'Word Of Mouth.' 

With new albums and mix compilations not to far away, and a whole host of new releases, Leftroom is sure to carry on where it left off which is delivering high quality, diverse dance music.

london.description:

- The Troubadour, London

-Chesney Hawkes, Singer/Songwriter 

“Laura Jeanne is lovely as the summers day. Beautiful in every way. Divine in her music and fashion, she's gonna have a mansion. She's got so much soul, and she's on a roll.You better watch out, ain't no doubt, Laura Jeanne gonna set your heart on fire with maximum desire! I should know, she's taken me higher! Awe yeah!! Supreme Congrats to you beautiful Laura Jeanne, on your love ride to number one all over this World. With love and respect, Narada Michael Walden”
- Narada Michael Walden, Grammy & Emmy Award Winning Producer, Musician & Recording Artist.

“Laura Jeanne a fantastic new talent! She has a powerful, lush voice and shows she can write catchy, fresh pop songs with her brilliant debut single ‘Coincidence’”
- Ian Greaves, Director Music Programming, Napster UK

“In a saturated industry, Laura Jeanne provides, through her angelic voice, a breath of fresh air” 
- Raef Bjayou, The Apprentice BBC ONE 

"Laura Jeanne has a beauty & honesty to her singing voice that won't fail to give her listeners goose-bumps. Her music is genuine and created with integrity, which she delivers consistently with her unique & stunning vocal talent." 
- Natasha Andrews, Vocalist (Chicane) & Vocal Coach

"Talent, love, determination and hard work, from these ingredients emerge the owned, true voice and music that is Laura Jeanne. " 
- Dee Johnson, Vocalist (Simply Red)

"Laura combines a strong vocal ability, a flair for song writing with a certain vulnerability and natural beauty- an enchanting recipe for international success.”
- Ashley Rossiter, Celebrity Stylist

For someone who didn’t realise they could sing until the age of 16, Singer, Songwriter & Fashion Designer, Laura Jeanne, has achieved a huge amount in a short space of time. Having taught herself to play the Guitar & Piano, songwriting naturally followed, and since then Laura has performed at some of London’s most prestigious venues, already had songs published by EMI, received critical acclaim from some of our most popular celebrities as well as industry chiefs, appeared as on US TV Show, ‘The Big Time’ on ABC and released 2 Singles, ‘Coincidence’, and ‘Dream, Believe Achieve’ which was sponsored by Budweiser. Laura has recently been chosen for BBC Introducing and her Debut Single, 'Coincidence' went straight into Napster's Hot 5 Featured Artists & New Releases alongside Bruno Mars and Lady Gaga. The Music Video for 'Coincidence' has been aired throughout the UK on Music Channels, and in High-Street Shops, Malls and Gyms.

On a trip to Scotland, inspired by the majesty of her surroundings Laura discovered a passion for poetry which soon led to songwriting. It was around the same time that Laura was teaching herself to play the guitar and piano, and having learnt Suzuki Violin from the age of 4, it seemed like a natural step for Laura to take, as her musical curiosity grew. 

Laura Jeanne’s unique sound has already caught the attention of an army of online fans including Grammy & Emmy Award Winning Producer, Narada Michael Walden, Singer/Songwriter Chesney Hawkes, and BBC Radio 2 and BBC 6 Music DJ, Bob Harris. Laura went on to prove to be a natural success on stage performing live at some of London’s trendiest nightspots including The Hard Rock Cafe, The Troubadour, Cafe De Paris, Chinawhite, The Bedford & Regal Room, as well as performing at home of The Beatles, The Cavern in Liverpool.

It hasn’t all been music for Laura though. A Fashion Degree from Hertfordshire University gave Laura the chance to develop skills that have led to her designing and making all the outfits she currently wears on stage and in her music videos. This has enabled her to create her truly unique signature style- a strong yet feminine mix of military mixed with romantic styles.

The need to fund her journey in the music business has also seen Laura Jeanne appear as an Extra & Actor in many major Films and TV Shows, including Harry Potter and The Deathly Hallows Part 2, Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows and Downton Abbey Series 2. She even has a stint as Anna Friel’s body double on her CV!

Having already achieved so much, and about to start writing her Debut Album in Nashville, Laura Jeanne is definitely one to watch.

london.name: Laura Jurd
london.description:
Laura Jurd is a trumpet player, composer and improviser from the UK.  A recipient of multiple awards and a BBC New Generation Artist from 2015-2017, Laura has developed a formidable reputation as one of the most distinctive and creative composer-performers to emerge from the UK in recent years.

Performing regularly throughout the UK and Europe, she leads the 2017 Mercury-nominated band Dinosaur who have performed at North Sea, Montreal and Molde International Jazz festivals to name a few. A highly active composer, Laura is equally at home writing for contemporary chamber groups and orchestras as she is writing for jazz ensembles and improvising musicians. Frequently creating works that present musical ingredients from outside the world of jazz music, within the realms of a jazz band, she has by been commissioned by the likes of the BBC Proms and the National Youth Jazz Orchestra, the BBC Concert Orchestra, Ligeti Quartet and the Northern Sinfonia.

A passionate educator, Laura also teaches composition at Trinity Laban Conservatoire of Music and Dance; jazz trumpet at Goldsmiths University and works with the National Youth Orchestra and the National Youth Jazz Collective.

london.name: Laura Harvey
london.description:
Laura Harvey is the founder of the female DJ team SpinSisters. SpinSisters is the Premier Weddings & Events DJ Service - https://www.spin-sisters.co.uk/

It's fair to say that Laura Harvey has burst on to the scene over the last twelve months. As a DJ, Laura Harvey has taken flight and soared in a very short space of time, working tirelessly to perfect her sets and develop her understanding of the crowd.

This agile selector has been delighting crowds at events across London, Berlin and Amsterdam with a mix of tech house, techno and progressive dance music. And it's her ability to delicately manoeuvre through these styles, playing to the moment that really sets her apart.

Key moments include  Faceless Recordings at IPSE, Berlin;  Motto at Basing house; Krafted and Decoded Records at Ministry of Sound but her ambition and skill has seen her secure a residency at London based night B4 (Basing House), as well regular sets at Krafted (Ministry of Sound & Egg), and also make her mark on the festival circuit, appearing at Lounge on the Lake and Shift Festival. The winter season looks no less active with sets confirmed for ADE, Halloween at EGG Club and the final B4 parties of the year.

With a dedication to the craft unlike many of her peers Laura Harvey will be making bigger waves in 2017. Plans to enter the studio are a natural target but for now she'll continue to delight crowds and focus on conducting dance floors. Watch out! Words by Leon Clarkson

birmingham.name: VIVa MUSiC Group
birmingham.description:
Demo Submission: https://tstack.app/viva-music-label-group-demos/send


Started in October 2006 by Steve Lawler, VIVa Music began life as a conduit for the internationally renowned DJ and Producer to release the wealth of underground music he encountered on his travels. Now, just a few years later VIVa is a self-contained hotbed for new talent which draws attention from DJs, punters and producers alike. Having previously handled the now-classic and traditional vinyl label Harlem Records, Lawler decided VIVa was to be a forward thinking outlet for quality music and boldly announced that VIVa was to be digital only. As well as a clear mission to look towards the future of the music industry, this was a step to ensure that music could be released quickly and retain the freshness that the labels A&R was struck by. Far from the template set out by many of Lawler's contemporaries, VIVa quickly established itself as a label where artists could be themselves and write music that isn't defined by just A&R, but by one simple guideline: Quality. This has meant the label has gone on to release music from a wide range artists, from major players like Lawler and Audiofly through to burgeoning talent like Livio & Roby and Nicole Moudaber. In keeping with an ever evolving outlook, 2009 will see VIVa further transformed. Worldwide tour nights, Festival Arena, International Residency's and a new UK based residency at the legendary Ministry of Sound in London are just the tip of the iceberg. Always ones to buck trends, the VIVa family are pressing vinyl again alongside it's digital output as well as expanding its roster of relatively unknown talent rather than rely on the tried and tested. At the forefront of this exclusive roster of talent are the likes of Vrajitoroo, David Pher, Dragosh, Adroid Cartel, Jimmy Hill, Alex Tepper, TRNNSTR, Darius Syrossian & NYRA, Erphun and Sean Miller but VIVa will continue to work with what it considers extended family for both releases as well as remixes; which means the likes of Jamie Jones, Audiofly, Simon Baker, Tiefschwarz, Bearweasel, David Durango and many, many more. VIVa is an important part of my life now, building a family of artists, that I take great pleasure in building and pushing. The amount of amazing music coming from new talent is phenomenal and its birth and direction are very exciting. - Steve Lawler Viva VIVa, 2010

Jungle Citizenz are a crew formed & based in Birmingham comprise of Craig Graham and Cheshire Cat MC.

It didn’t take long for ravers to like their sound and top producers from around the world have given them some fantastic support and advice, especially their very own mic controller Cheshire Cat . Cheshire travels around with the lads jumping on the mic from time to time. So the lads then decided to bring in Cheshire as a permanent fixture as his voice really lends itself perfectly to their sound . Cheshire is a vastly experienced mc with some of the biggest sound systems around the country and has worked with the mighty Leftfield, and has a platinum disc to prove his success and so  it was sealed Cheshire Cat was now a member of the Jungle Citizenz .

Craig Graham  has around 20 years experience playing on the fringes of the scene and was one of the leading Dj’s on the legendary pirate radio station Starlight fm. Craig is the tech head of the crew and works on all formats and is the key to  new underground sounds.

Cheshire Cat born and bred in Birmingham,started chatting the mic in 1982 for local sounds like ITAL WARRIOR and NYAHTONE HIFI.

In 1988 Cat Joined LOVE INJECTION SOUND,Clashing with othe sounds like SAXON,SIR COXSONE and V-ROCKE.
In these clashes Cat would hold the mic and tear up the dance everytime,also clashing from yard like STONE LOVE,GEMINI,SILVER HAWK and JARO to name a few…

2012 sees Cheshire Cat crossing over to the JUNGLE/DRUM N BASS scene and making an immediate impact working alongside top artists CHOPSTICK DUBPLATE crew Aries,Jacky Murda & Tuffist as well as Jungle Citizenz,Mr Williamz,Daddy Freddy,David Boomah,Congo Natty,

The best party songs ever made offer nonstop beats and are certified bangers that’ll heat up any dancefloor. This is top priority for the U.K’s rising mashup Kings Catchfraze & Zapdos. The duo made up of Brandon and Ben are two highly energetic DJ/producers who have been known to tear down the walls and raise the roofs in clubs & festivals across the U.K. & Europe with their high energy main room and mashup shows. 
Notably one of the U.K’s most sought-after DJ’s, Catchfraze & Zapdos have it nailed creating unique and exciting mashups of artists like Joel Corry, Chris Brown, Deorro, David Guetta, Jauz, Macky Gee and more. sprinkling their sets with an exciting high energy flip whilst owning their explosive live shows across the country - (Always expect the unexpected).

With a catalogue of over 200 songs uploaded to record pools such as TheMashup, Digital DJ Pool, DJ City and more. The boys haven’t taken the slow road when it comes to electronic music but instead have ruthlessly spent hours upon hours taking their sound and their style right where it needs to be, on dance floors and in the playlists of fellow electronic artists.

While proudly boasting 23x Top 10's Releases on TheMashup, 12x Top 10's Releases on Digital DJ Pool and 15x Top 10's Releases on Hypeddit, their chart topping Mashups & Mashup Packs have saw their fair share of rotation across dancefloors with over 50,000 Downloads!, With their most notable mashup “Pump Up De Samba” being one of the most played tracks in the U.K. in 2021.

On the road with a fully loaded live tour and guest slots across the country, the U.K’s Mashup Kings set fire to venues across Europe and very rarely get to see their own beds! From stages U.K. wide to clubs and festivals across Europe it’s safe to say the Party never stops!

birmingham.name: Gwyddion Flint (Xanadüüm)
birmingham.description:
British interdisciplinary artist, writer and synth musician. 

Please check out my music videos on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@gwyddionflint -The likes and subscribes help me get my music out here through the algorithm.

Blurb: Gwyddion has exhibited his artwork nationally in the U.K. and is now beginning to exhibit internationally, along with his poetry and other writing currently available through Amazon and publishing platform Medium. His artwork is heavily influenced by Buddhism, philosophy, psychology and future technologies. Previous works have included psycho-geographical and hoax art elements, such as the Hopwas Project, where he buried two copper plates and other occult artifacts in a Staffordshire woodland that were later found and written about in local newspapers and online, sparking an interest into the woodland’s past that became international. Despite some of the more elaborate artworks and installations that he has created he always comes back to pencil drawing, poetry and prose as his main source of inspiration. His poetry is primarily created as spoken word works to be accompanied by synth soundscapes and imagery, both live and recorded.
 
The film ‘Brutalist’, a contemporary dance, electronic music and spoken word film was created by ‘Collabs’, a London based platform (headed by producer Dan Lowenstein) for arts collaboration of all kinds, utilising the poem ‘In the City of My Body’ to create an experimental film and dance work in 2018. He has also collaborated with David Tibet from the experimental band ‘Current 93’ in creating a sound installation in the south of England. He is a qualified yoga instructor and practices and teaches vipassana meditation which he studied while living in a Buddhist monastery for a year as a monk and later while living and traveling in South East Asia and India, where he also learned other yogic practices which inform his art

His musical influences include: Tangerine Dream, Vangelis, John Carpenter, Current 93, Genesis P Orridge, Enigma, Mike Oldfield, Robert Miles and Keith Emerson.

birmingham.name: Paul-F (Studio engineer)
birmingham.description:
Paul-F is name that may be familiar to some of you now on the Underground dance scene with releases (and as a signed artist) on many of the major labels such as New State (Amnesia Future Trance Anthems), Lethal Theory (Signed artist), Bionic, Tidy, Awsum, Traffic, Riot, Presence and B2T recordings and many more covering other genres also.
In his studio, Paul has Gone from strength to strength crafting his reputation as a very hard working studio engineer who's capabilities and 'final product' sound quality where spotted by some truly respected International artists and labels who approached Paul to work on remixes or collaborations with them.
Rob Tissera (Owner of the worldwide House event KISSDAFUNK/ International DJ),  Joey Riot (Multi award winning DJ/ Owner of Lethal Theory, UK Hardcore's No.1 Label), Marc Smith (Scotland's No.1 DJ voted 7 times), Amber D (International DJ/ Label Owner) are a few to date with more projects planned for the future.

Dominating download charts on numerous occasions and receiving National Radio 1 support into the double figures now of Paul's tracks so far, is testimonial in itself to his capabilities and flexibility as an artist.
More recently Paul has turned his attentions to the EDM scene, encompassing anything from House to Trance, fusing them together with his own uplifting and unique style. 
His first attempt on this genre was picked up by New State records and featured on the Amnesia future trance album with his remix (Under his Senction-8 alias) of Quake & Rob Tissera’s anthem, “The day will come”, alongside scene leaders like Ferry corsten, Armin Van Buren, BT, Cosmic gate and Paul Van Dyk to name a few, showing Paul is more than capable of delivering the goods and might just be one to watch! 

As a DJ, Paul's highly energetic persona shines through in his performances and has destroyed dance floors up and down the country and further afield. Playing his own individual style fusing drive with euphoria, Paul's shown time and time again that he's equally at home in the DJ box, in front of hundreds or thousands, as he is sat in the studio. 
With name and reputation building, some of the following known brands on the Underground dance music scene have given him the opportunity to do what he loves most at some major events up and down the U.K and abroad,  Slammin vinyl (Sanctuary festival) HTID in the sun 2011 (Spain) B2T, Storm, Insomiacz, Polysexual, Sundissential, Pams House, Ravers Are, Frantic (tour),Summit are just a tiny fraction of his bookings to date.

"Thank you all so much for all your support up to this point, I'm honestly humbled by some of your messages and comments, makes it all worthwhile so thank you. 
I've met so many amazing people doing what I do I couldn't imagine stopping this for a long time to come so, if you like what you've heard so far, stick around ,cause the best is yet to come".

Thanks for stopping by, 

Paul :0)

Here's the link to my all new EDM focused Soundcloud, please take a moment to follow me over there if you like it a little lighter on the bpm ;0)
Thanks again guys, much respect!
http://soundcloud.com/falseprofitrecordings

birmingham.name: Martin Ford (DD:MF)
birmingham.description:
Martin Ford’s career started out as most DJ’s do, as a clubber regularly frequenting Bakers in Birmingham. It’s here where he was introduced to the sounds of the DJ’s and Brands that would start to shape his career. With the likes of Richie Roberts at Love Sexy on Fridays, Scott Bond at Republica on Saturdays and Decadence on Wednesdays Martin was exposed to some of the most diverse music going around the UK in the early 90’s, He credits Sasha and Digweed as major inspiration and you can hear this echo through into his style today.
Martin was soon itching to get out and play, in 1996 he landed his first gig at The Attic in Birmingham. In 1998 Godskitchen offered up a residency alongside legend Chris Turner where he supported the biggest names in trance and house at the time keeping his residency for 3 years (no mean feat at a huge brand like that). 
Martin was also resident of B1 at bakers for 2 years too, there is not a venue in Birmingham, maybe even the midlands that Martin has not played in. In addition, 3 years of main season parties on Kavos for Limelight and Chequers. 
Martin also played Godskitchen summer ball at Milton Keynes in front of 6500 clubbers sandwiched between John Kelly and Tall Paul.
In 2002 Martin decided it was time to concentrate on other ventures and family and took a step back from the music scene. 
In early 2013, at a night called ME in Birmingham Martin played his first set in 11 years. He must have been bitten by the bug again as since then he has gone on to play as a headline for Birmingham brand Enter The Dragon and Presents a weekly show on Lockedinradio. 
July 2016 Martin became first resident of Anomaly in Birmingham where he has supported the likes of Thrillseekers, Matt Darey, Airwave, Agnelli & Nelson, Craig Connelly, Jordan Suckley, Ben Nicky and Jorn van Deynhoven to name but a few. 
In 2017 Martin took another step in his career by jumping into production with Dan Deas forming DD:MF who debuted their first track ‘Nymeria’ at Anomaly to a roar of screams from an adoring crowd. The track then went on to be remixed by Carl Nicholson and signed to Art Recordings. 
The future looks good for this legend of the scene.

birmingham.name: Russell G
birmingham.description:
It is no wonder that Russell G has featured at various venues around the world representing brands including Godskitchen, Global Gathering and Sander Van Doorn’s ‘Dusk Til Doorn’, all entrusting Russell to deliver his uplifting and energetic sound to their audiences.

Russell’s big breakthrough came from the mighty Godskitchen where he made his debut at Godskitchen’s Global Gathering on their flagship Boombox stage alongside Armin Van Buuren, Eric Prydz & Sasha.

It’s not just Russell’s DJ’ing that has seen him earn acclaim. Russell has been behind many underground anthems and his eclectic style as seen him release on a wide range of labels. ‘The Real Life’ on Spinnin, ‘3AM’ & ‘Solstice’ on Armada, ‘Free For All’, ‘Rush’ & Russell’s collab with Marco V ‘Kalevala’ on Marco’s own In Charge imprint saw Beatport success.

2014 saw Russell revisit his very early musical influences with the result being his music developing a trancier edge with great success to date with the highlight being Russell reaching #4 in the Beatport Trance Top 100 chart with his cover of ‘Cafe Del Mar’ whilst tracks ‘Mantra’ & ‘Shimmer’ also charted highly. Russell has enjoyed support in 2014 from artists including Gareth Emery, Max Graham, Ferry Corsten & Lange to name but a few.

2015 has continued in the same way 2014 finished as his single ‘Skala’ has been signed to Paul Van Dyk’s Vandit Records, his track ‘Fiji’ being supported by Armin on his ASOT show and his remix of Paul Oakenfold ‘Hold That Sucker Down’ seeing a release Perfecto.

Russell is also the driving force behind the growing ‘Music Matters Recordings’ imprint, the label is a true reflection of the music he loves whilst striving to give artists a platform to showcase their talents, the label continues to go from strength to strength which is reflected in Beatport chart positions and support from Above & Beyond, Gai Barone, M.I.K.E & more.

birmingham.name: Ewura Abena Muisq
birmingham.description:
Gospel Ministrel/Composer-Songwriter/CEO: EA Multimedia Limited.
Booking: +233202400054


Ewura Abena is a Ghanaian born gospel singer / songwriter and an entrepreneur based in the UK. Officially known as Vida Ewura Abena Yeboah, Ewura Abena is the 5th of the 6 children of Rev Prince & the late Mrs. Mary Ohene –Asare.

Ewura Abena had her early childhood education in Takoradi and Asamakese, respectively and continued to Abuakwa State College in Kibi, Ghana. She later enrolled at the Ghana Institute of Journalism to study Communication Studies. Then to  Cambridge International College, London to pursued Administration and Human Resource Management.

Ewura Abena is now studying  to become a Diagnostic Ultrasound Sonographer.

She is very passionate about  music and started singing at a very tender age in the year 1996. She released her first studio album dubbed “Kama Kama” in 2009. The album featured her hit song “Agye Me Nkwa” (featuring Nacee) which  catapulted her into instant stardom with numerous appearances at events countrywide.

She followed it up with two other albums, “Eye” and “All I Say”, and then a couple of singles. 

 In life her sole role model is CHRIST whom Paul admonishes all to emulate.
She writes and  sings about God and his blessings upon humanity. Ewura Abena Has never been afraid to write songs about difficult situations. 

“ These difficult times make my writing and compositions  rather intense. Writing songs in my difficult moments is my way of coping but it is not at all a sad story.”


 The multitalented musician, is a wife, a mother of two and still expecting more. 
Ewura Abena has a Cosmetic and Beauty Product line and company, Ewurabelle Collections, based in the UK.

Luke Simpson, better known as Simmo, is a highly skilled house DJ and producer from Birmingham, United Kingdom. With a special focus on Tech House music, he delivers an unparalleled sound experience that is perfect for any type of venue.

Born in the late 90s, Simmo was raised around a diverse range of music from an early age. At just eight years old, he discovered house music and was captivated by its infectious energy and versatility. He dreamed of playing at some of the biggest EDM festivals in the world, including Tomorrowland and Coachella.

Simmo cites a number of influential artists in the house genre as his inspirations, including Pawsa, Michael Bibi, John Summit, Sidney Charles, Hitty, Archie Hamilton, and Chris Stussy. While he has developed his own unique style of mixing and playing, his later passion for creating and delivering music was heavily influenced by these legends.

Simmo's dedication and talent have earned him numerous opportunities to perform at various gigs and events internationally; showcasing his exceptional range of skills and impressive references. He is proud to be a part of Vibe City's upcoming events in 2024 and is excited to bring his signature sound to audiences across the globe.

For more information on Simmo, bookings, and upcoming events, please visit his instagram: @simmo.uk

birmingham.name: Gwyddion Flint (Xanadüüm)
birmingham.description:
British interdisciplinary artist, writer and synth musician. 

Please check out my music videos on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@gwyddionflint -The likes and subscribes help me get my music out here through the algorithm.

Blurb: Gwyddion has exhibited his artwork nationally in the U.K. and is now beginning to exhibit internationally, along with his poetry and other writing currently available through Amazon and publishing platform Medium. His artwork is heavily influenced by Buddhism, philosophy, psychology and future technologies. Previous works have included psycho-geographical and hoax art elements, such as the Hopwas Project, where he buried two copper plates and other occult artifacts in a Staffordshire woodland that were later found and written about in local newspapers and online, sparking an interest into the woodland’s past that became international. Despite some of the more elaborate artworks and installations that he has created he always comes back to pencil drawing, poetry and prose as his main source of inspiration. His poetry is primarily created as spoken word works to be accompanied by synth soundscapes and imagery, both live and recorded.
 
The film ‘Brutalist’, a contemporary dance, electronic music and spoken word film was created by ‘Collabs’, a London based platform (headed by producer Dan Lowenstein) for arts collaboration of all kinds, utilising the poem ‘In the City of My Body’ to create an experimental film and dance work in 2018. He has also collaborated with David Tibet from the experimental band ‘Current 93’ in creating a sound installation in the south of England. He is a qualified yoga instructor and practices and teaches vipassana meditation which he studied while living in a Buddhist monastery for a year as a monk and later while living and traveling in South East Asia and India, where he also learned other yogic practices which inform his art

His musical influences include: Tangerine Dream, Vangelis, John Carpenter, Current 93, Genesis P Orridge, Enigma, Mike Oldfield, Robert Miles and Keith Emerson.

birmingham.name: Emma Margetson
birmingham.description:
Emma Margetson (1993) is an acousmatic composer and sound artist with extensive experience in multichannel composition, sound diffusion and interpretation. She has received a variety of awards and special mentions for her work including, first prize in the prestigious L'Espace du Son International Spatialisation Competition by INFLUX (Musiques & Recherches), klingt gut! Young Artist Award in 2018 and Ars Electronica Forum Wallis 2019.

Emma’s compositional work is focused on developing novel compositional approaches that are actively geared towards increasing engagement with acousmatic/electroacoustic composition in order to reach wider audiences, in particular disadvantaged segments of the community, and younger people. Having recently completed a PhD in Musical Composition funded by the AHRC Midlands3Cities Doctoral Training Partnership titled ‘Sonic Immersion: Reaching New Audiences through Sound’, Emma has collaborated with a variety of organisations including the IKON gallery, Research & Cultural Collections at the University of Birmingham and The Barber Institute of Fine Arts.

Her works have been performed and exhibited internationally, including at Ars Electronica Forum Wallis (CH), University of Birmingham (UK), The Barber Institute of Fine Arts (UK), 5to Festival de Música Electroacústica (CL), BEAST FEaST (UK), SEAMUS (USA), CEMI circles (USA), EMAS (UK), Festival Ecos Urbanos (MEX), BULO (UK), RMA (UK), SPECTRA (CO), NYCEMF (USA), Birmingham Hippodrome (UK), Audior Acusmonium (ITL), Sound-Image Colloquium (UK), Delian Academy of New Music (GD), Noisefloor Festival (UK), [ ex_nihilo ] (MEX), MAtera INtermedia (ITL), Sound Junction (UK), Musica Electronic Nova (PL) and Electric Spring (UK).

She has compositions released with labels Urban Arts Belin, Sonos Localia and Obs.

birmingham.name: Angela Elizabeth Slater
birmingham.description:
Dr. Angela Elizabeth Slater is a UK-based composer, whose compositional voice focuses on musically mapping aspects of the natural world into the fabric of music. Nominated for an Ivors Classical Award for her work, Through the Fading Hour, her music has been described as ‘intricate...and often ravishingly scored’ and  making ‘deft and vivid use of instrumental colour’.. Slater collaborates with performers, ensembles, and initiatives worldwide to musically explore sounds, colours, and textures.

Slater’s recent creative projects include fellowships at the Modern Music Festival, with performances of Glass dominoes for mixed ensemble and Gathering the tide for orchestra; Hong Kong Intimacy of Creativity Festival, working with the Viano Quartet on Distorted Light; Santa Fe Chamber Music Festival, for a commission of Where skies aflame, written for the Flux quartet; and Creative Dialogues Festival, for the world premiere of a tulip, iron. She has previously held Composition Fellowships at Tanglewood Music Center, London Philharmonic Orchestra, Royal Philharmonic Society, Royal Scottish National Orchestra Composers’ Hub, Stockholm Chamber Brass Academy, Impulse Festival, Young Composers Meeting. She is also the receipt of the Mendelssohn Scholarship Award and is an ISCM World Music Days Nominee.

Unravelling the Crimson Sky will be a featured work on the City of Birmingham Symphony Orchestra’s upcoming album, Sounds New. Additional upcoming collaborations include Arbor Concerto, a consortium for accordion and chamber orchestra led by Sanja Mlinarič, Mountains become oceans, a consortium for percussion and harp led by Rosanna Moore and Hannah Weaver, and an expansion of As the moon runs red into a trumpet concerto with wind ensemble led by Simon Debruslais. Past collaboration highlights include working with Laura Farré Rozada  and the Royal Birmingham Conservatoire Symphony Orchestra on piano concerto, Tautening skies and with Richard Waters and the London Philharmonic Orchestra on the world premiere of her viola concerto, Through the fading hour.

​Slater is also the Director of Illuminate Women’s Music, a chamber music concert series designed to celebrate the creativity of women composers and performers, as well as exploring the rich legacy of music written by women historically. Her works are self-published, with select works published by Composers Edition and Babel Scores. Please visit https://www.angelaslatercomposer.co.uk/ for more information.
For more information please visit: https://angelaslatercomposer.co.uk

glasgow.description:
Vixen Sound is a Scottish soundsystem culture selector and radio show raggamuffin. 

Having shared stages with the likes or Aba Shanti I, Iration Steppas, Manudigital, Dubkasm, and David Rodigan, Vixen has played across the world from India to New York, and runs several club nights across Scotland. Working closely with Mungo's Hi Fi on the running of their record label, Scotch Bonnet Records. Vixen Sound is also part of the Sinai Sound System family. Currently a resident on Glasgow's Clydebuilt FM, Vixen has previously hosted shows on LVLZ Radio &  Subcity Radio, and presents a new-music show on BBC Radio Scotland each Friday night.

glasgow.name: Rylan Gleave
glasgow.description:
Rylan Gleave (b.1997) is a Glasgow-based composer and vocalist whose music addresses intersectional identity, re-contextualised natural situations, and quiet, furious resistance. His musical practice is inclusive, and involves mending the unfeigned gaps in his classical study with the healings of imaginative neuro-/ gender-divergent kinship.
Re-emerging as a composer/performer, Rylan’s work explores the instrumental qualities of his late-breaking trans-masc voice through queer autoethnography, and autistic-specific notation. His music has been praised as ‘haunting’ by The Herald, and ‘rapturous’ by The Scotsman, who named him ‘One to Watch’ 2021, describing him as ‘one of the brightest lights in Scotland’s new music scene’. Rylan has recently graduated from an MMus Degree with Dr. Linda Buckley at the Royal Conservatoire of Scotland, with the Royal Conservatoire of Scotland Composition prize and The Craig Armstrong Prize, after completing his BMus with David Fennessy, graduating with Honours of the First Class, The Dinah and Walter Wolfe Memorial Award, and The Kimie Composition Prize.

glasgow.name: McKellar
glasgow.description:
Hailing from Glasgow McKellar is singer/songwriter/producer David McKellar. No stranger to the industry having already supported acts such as Shed 7 at Glasgow’s O2 Academy and world famous Barrowland Ballroom.

In recent years David has worked with lots of different musicians including the Verve legends Nick McCabe and Si Jones, David Rossi of Goldfrapp and Coldplay, Mig (Portishead) Amelia Tucker now all members of Black Submarine. This collaboration would see his outstanding vocals on the track "Rope Soul’d" which would make it onto the John Martyn tribute album, Johnny boy would love this. This contribution would sit along side artists such as Beck, the cure and Paolo Nutini.
Vocals also on Hector Bizerk track "Seldom a word we don't say too often" from the Nobody seen nothing album.
Other pervious collaborations have included work with Paul Banks (Shed 7), Stu Fletcher (Seahorses) and Maxi (Audioweb and drummer for Ian Brown pre Stone Roses reunion).
An impressive array of contributions and collaborations that secure his steady rise up the ranks.

Singer McKellar also plays the drums, guitar and bass and has a wealth of experience in all aspects of production having mixed, recorded and produced such acts like the Twilight Sad. The demos which helped them land their record deal.

Influenced by acts such as The Beatles, The Rolling Stones, Neil Young, Crosby, Stills and Nash and Young. Buffalo Springfield. David's material has been causing quite a storm on the Glasgow music scene gaining him a loyal legion of fans and a huge amount of recognition, such as Camglen Radio having him as their Featured Artist of The Week, all in such a short space of time.

glasgow.name: Paul Ross
glasgow.description:
I'm a DJ from Glasgow, Scotland and my journey through the genres has seen me provide the soundtrack at pool-side bars in the Middle East, alongside regular slots on Beach-Radio.co.uk and Glasgow's very own Groove City Radio.

During the initial COVID-19 lockdown in 2020, I dusted off my turntables and started Livestreaming my ‘Quay Mix Series’ every fortnight on social media, and uploading the sets online. In early July 2020, the team at Beach-Radio.co.uk allocated me a weekly slot for my ‘Quay Beach Mixes’ series, and just a few weeks later it was announced that I had finished as a runner up in the ‘Sir Ivan Megamix’ competition, where my set was judged by Paul Oakenfold, Bass Jackers, DJs from Mars, Tenisha, and Exodus.

In the summer of 2022 I started my journey with Groove City Radio! My show 'The Quay Sessions' is on every 4th Wednesday at 6-8pm!

glasgow.name: Sharkey's Machine
glasgow.description:
Over the last 20 years i have held residencies at the world famous Sub Club in Glasgow, Mas, with Glasgow Disco King Billy Woods & various secret after-hours venues all over the city of Glasgow, particularly a certain one on Bridge Street, after a Pressure party, in olden times.

In Europe i have held a residency on the Electro Juice Boat in Bordeaux for 15 years and at the Wunderboat soiree's on Bordeaux's premier venue, The IBoat. 

My biggest influences are local legends Subculture, of Sub Club, Glasgow, where i've covered warm ups and closing slots for residents Harri and Domenic, my other main and equal influence is Slam, particularly during the Daft Punk years, me having ran their promo in the mid 90's and being part of their team that started and promoted the Pressure party in the late 90's.

Although i have also ran a lot of my own nights alongside managing the promotions team at the Sub Club for 10 years, it's the love and joy in performance that keeps bringing me back to being behind the turntables and playing records as a form of artistic expression.

Having lived in Den Haag Netherlands for some time, i am now back in Glasgow and available for bookings.

For booking requests please contact: jacquib1001@aol.com

Something definitely worth checking is a new night and concept - Passenger, an intimate, safespace, underground dance music experience that takes place in very unique and always interesting new venues in the city of Glasgow - Please go check out what all the fuss is about, you will be made to feel most welcome and amongst like minded, musical people!

glasgow.name: AJAY C
glasgow.description:
AJAY C has had a love for music since the early nineties. Digging through his brothers cassette tapes listening to Gangsta Rap – ICE T – NWA – PUBLIC ENEMY.  Around this era is when AJAY C started hitting up the INFAMOUS underage nightclub scene in Glasgow – ARCHAOS -THE SUB CLUB – THE TUNNEL. 

Fascinated by the dance scene and his love of buying vinyl, led him to get his first set of decks when he was 16. Experiencing the clubbing haven at THE ARCHES, Glasgow and falling in love with Trance, House and Techno. Raving week in and week out to the likes of MAURO PICOTTO – BEN SIMS – CARL COX – LAURENT GARNIER – ROBERT HOOD. A large influence on the WAX he was buying and hosting parties around discotheques in Glasgow. 

With over two decades of experience under his belt. NOW, If he’s not locking down the INFAMOUS AFTERS in Glasgow. You can can catch him warming up for special guests like Paul Birken, Thomas Schumacher and The Yellowheads. Still to this day he has a love for VINYL and now is the RESIDENT DJ and HEAD HONCHO of Glasgow underground outfit TAIKANO. Hosting upcoming cutting edge international and local talent.

Expect him to take you on a musical journey dropping Techno, Acid, House, Rave, EBM and Hard Trance along the way.

glasgow.name: Properoldskool
glasgow.description:
Proper Oldskool are redefining the word oldskool, with up to date exclusive bootlegs & mash ups interpreted into their energetic sets, Paul D, DJ Oldskool & JB have entertained and inspired crowds young and old(skool) whereever they go.

Their fresh outlook on the oldskool vibe has helped keep their sets different to many oldskool DJ's, blowing up venues and festivals since they started gigging in 2009. They really hit the map in Summer 2009 when they headlined the Boombus at T In The park on the Saturday night and were voted on Forth FM as a highlight at T In The Park ( pretty awesome considering the line up that year) as as a result were booked to headline the Boombus again in 2010.... the only time an artist has headlined T In The Park 2 years in a row.

The boys also supported The Complete Stone Roses 2 years in a row on the Scottish leg of their UK tours and were personally asked by the band to remix their track " Tell Me Moses" in 2009. 

Events played so far include : T In The Park, EH1, Fantazia, Rezerection, Fantasylands, Coloursfest, Judgement Day, Anthem City & Selektance. 

The proper Oldskool DJ's are : Paul D, DJ Tony Oldskool & JB. Each bring a uniquie talent to the table and this is what makes this DJ team the best Oldskool DJ's in the UK.

glasgow.name: Eddie Kitsner
glasgow.description:
Biography of Eddie Kitsner: Unleashing the Underground Groove
Eddie Kitsner, a name resonating in the heart of the underground dance world, is more than just a music producer; he's a sonic architect crafting vibrant, pulsating beats that reverberate through the souls of his listeners. With an unwavering dedication to his craft and an insatiable passion for music, Eddie has embarked on a journey that has made him a force to be reckoned with in the realm of electronic music.
The Genesis of a Musical Odyssey
In the year 2020, Eddie rekindled his musical odyssey, stepping back into the studio with a newfound vigor. Armed with a fresh perspective, innovative workflow, and a treasure trove of electrifying beats, he set out to redefine his sound. His goal was clear: to create an original signature sound that would captivate the global underground dance scene.
Mastering the Art of Sonic Alchemy
From the age of 20, Eddie was drawn into the hypnotic world of mixing, and there was no turning back. Over the course of 24 years, he meticulously honed his skills, transforming himself into a maestro behind the decks. His unique blend of deep tech house, Afro house, and tech house seamlessly weaves together, building a sonic tapestry that takes the audience on a mesmerizing journey. With a fusion of deep kicks, pulsating bass, and percussion that drives the crowd, Eddie orchestrates an experience that lingers in the hearts of all who surrender to his beats.
A Symphony of Collaborations
Eddie's musical prowess extends beyond his solo endeavors. He has collaborated with renowned artists from around the globe, including Marcel Ei Gio and Paul Di Gio from Argentina, as well as Joao Joaquim DJ Deep Noise from Portugal. These collaborations have not only expanded his creative horizons but have also enriched the global dance music landscape.
Setting the Dance Floors Ablaze
Currently signed to esteemed record labels such as Hexagonal Music,BBop Music,Arey,Layer Caked Melodic,Sound Optix,Confessions From The Underground Records,Deep People Records,A3 Music Sneja Recordings, and Bonzai Back Catalogue, Eddie's tracks have found their way into the playlists of underground enthusiasts worldwide. His affiliation with labels like Confessions from the Underground Records, SumSycheSynth Records, and LW Recordings further attests to his influence in shaping the contemporary electronic music scene.
The Journey Ahead
As Eddie Kitsner continues to evolve and innovate, his sonic expedition shows no signs of slowing down. With each beat, he pushes boundaries, leaving an indelible mark on the underground dance world. As he forges ahead, his dedication to crafting unparalleled music remains unyielding.
Follow Eddie Kitsner's mesmerizing beats on Beatport, and prepare to be swept away by the pulsating rhythms and infectious energy that define his musical odyssey. Experience the groove, embrace the rhythm, and join Eddie Kitsner on a journey through the very soul of electronic music.
EDDIE RELUCHES 
KITSNERS KUTZ Podcast! 🎧 
 Formerly known as The Tech House Podcast we're back with a fresh vibe, new energy, and amazing artists from around the world. I'm Eddie Kitsner, your host, and I'm thrilled to introduce you to a diverse range of electronic music genres, from tech house to techno, soulful deep house, organic house, downtempo, and more. 
 What to Expect: Expect nothing but the best electronic beats, featuring both established DJs and up-and-coming talents. Our mixes are carefully curated to bring the clubbing experience directly to your headphones, iPod, or car stereo. Get ready for a musical journey that transcends boundaries and genres!

glasgow.name: Paul Trainer
glasgow.description:
Trance / Tech / Progressive

Label:  Vandit / ITWT / ASOT / Discover / Spellbinding

Biography:

Paul has always had a passion for music at an early age, but it wasn't until 2001 that he bought himself his first set of decks after coming back inspired and influenced from the sounds of the Miami Winter Music Conference. Being a keen clubber himself, this led to attendance at all the well known festivals and gigs in the U.K and beyond, so as the years progressed Paul got more and more into modern day dance music.

To date, Paul has performed at some of Scotland’s top clubs including the Arches, Gatecrasher @ Room At The Top, Byblos, Sea, Blue, Keller Club and The Soundhaus, whilst also making his first international appearance’s in Ireland, Germany, Australia, New Zealand, 2 interstate tours of India and a Spellbinding Records label night in the USA, alongside artists such as Armin van Buuren, Above & Beyond, Andy Moor, Rank 1, Bryan Kearney, Ronski Speed, Sied van Riel, Organ Donors, Activa and Indecent Noise to name a few. Not limiting himself to one style, Paul’s sets feature rigorous tune selection which vary across the trance spectrum depending on the interaction with the crowd.

Paul promoted his own nights with a few friends in Glasgow such as Vibe, Synergy, Platinum and Rehab. With their main aim to offer something different to the Scottish clubbers, this resulted in several Scottish debut’s for the likes of John O’Callaghan, Aly & Fila, Menno de Jong, Giuseppe Ottaviani (Live), Stoneface & Terminal, Thomas Bronzwaer, Mat Zo, Amir Hussain, Chris Liebing, Anderson Noise, Axel Karakasis and Eric Sneo.

As a producer Paul’s tracks and remixes can be found under the mighty Dutch Armada stable on imprints such as A State Of Trance, Captivating Sounds, Coldharbour Recordings, Aropa Records, S107, fellow Dutch label Black Hole Recordings under their In Trance We Trust imprint and also on UK label’s Discover and Infrasonic Recordings. Featured several times on German label Vandit Records, some of the highlight’s include Paul’s first track ‘Totality’ which received big plays from Tiesto and  Paul van Dyk at the Winter Music Conference in Miami. ’Seize The Day’ was featured on Markus Schulz Top 40 of 2009, ‘Deal With It’ claimed the No.1 spot on the Trackitdown Top 100 Trance Chart, whilst also having remixed for Armada A-listers Markus Schulz, Dash Berlin and Dutch tech-trance masters Ernesto vs. Bastian. Paul’s tracks have gained huge support from the highest Dj elite including air plays on respected radio shows such as ASOT, Vonyc Sessions, Club Life, TATW, Corsten’s Countdown, GDJB, Planet Perfecto and BBC Radio 1. To date they have featured on CD compilations such as Cream, Godskitchen, Armada & Slinky.

Paul’s ‘Soundscape’ radio show is now in its 6th year and showcases the latest in trance, tech and progressive. You can tune in exclusively on Afterhours FM - www.ah.fm - 4th Tuesday of every month - (3pm GMT / 4pm CET).

2010 saw the launch of Paul's new record label 'Spellbinding Records' which crosses the boundaries of trance, techno, progressive and everything in between. With an ever growing scene of new dance music producers that go unnoticed, the main objective at Spellbinding is to unearth some new talent from the UK and beyond and get their tunes out there. The label will also feature some familiar names that are at the forefront of today’s scene. Massive support has been received so far from all the major players. Stay tuned for forthcoming releases at www.spellbindingrecords.co.uk .

glasgow.name: John J White
glasgow.description: A veteran of Glasgow’s thriving indie scene in the eighties, JJ White was the songwriter and guitarist of The Wiseacres: the Cherry Red debutantes who gained notable praise from such artists as Felt, Close Lobsters and the Monochrome Set. The group produced a sound body of work until their disbanding as the eighties came to a close. Following a brief stint in Mouse Eat Mouse in the aughts where he penned the music for their most praised LP ‘Mair Licht’ and a reunion of the Wiseacres in 2013, White sought to reinvent himself as a solo artist. He got to work on his debut album ‘An Ocean of Space’ in collaboration with his producer Colin ‘Soapy’ Cameron in 2019. His current sound (recommended for fans of Damien Jurado, Bonnie “Prince” Billy and Beck) is a delicate blend of lavish and thoughtful balladry with easy going Velvet Underground-esqe folk rock. He is presently in a place where most artists wish they could be as he reinvents himself as an artist with no need to conform to expectations and no sign of stopping soon.

MGMT/Bookings:

LINKS:
linttr.ee/SHVDZ

SHVDZ, pronounced "shades" are a UK based DJ & Production Duo comprised of Reece Ginestri and John Connor. SHVDZ's journey through music together begins at 16 years old when the pair were attending the same music production course whilst still in high-school. On the very first day they quickly discovered their mutual love for Blasterjaxx's big room classic "Fifteen". 2 weeks after their initial meeting, Reece's family moved house and as fate would have it, their new home just happened to be on the same street as John. From this point onwards, the pair began to work on music together and in 2020, SHVDZ was born. 

After their introduction to the EDM world in 2020 with releases on Lowded Recordings, Soave Records & Diverge Recordings, SHVDZ have been refining their signature sound. The SHVDZ sound takes inspiration from many different styles, with their latest tracks fusing elements from Techno, Trance and Progressive.

In 2023, SHVDZ debuted their new style with their remix of the Portuguese hit ‘Sentir Saudade’ alongside EDM heavyweight Kura on Tiësto's AFTR:HRS imprint. This was quickly followed up with their first ever Techno EP: ‘Eternity’ on Reload Records.

SHVDZ are kicking off 2024 with a bang with their new track ‘Do My Thing’ dropping on EXTATIC Records. Maddix has been a big inspiration for SHVDZ so to be releasing their 1st track of 2024 on his label feels like the perfect start to what is looking like is going to be a big year for the duo. Watch this space..

glasgow.name: Last Thrill
glasgow.description:
Last Thrill, the brainchild of Glasgow-based artist Darren Russell, is a one-man powerhouse dedicated to crafting a distinctive sound within the realm of synth-pop. Channeling the spirit of iconic 80s bands like Depeche Mode, Tears for Fears, and Daryl Hall & John Oates, Last Thrill seamlessly blends nostalgic influences with modern production sensibilities.

Darren, as the sole force behind Last Thrill, not only lends his soulful voice to the project but also takes charge of songwriting and production. Hailing from the vibrant music scene of Scotland, he weaves together massive synth-pop beats that pulsate with energy, setting the stage for anthemic choruses that demand attention.

The magic of Last Thrill lies in its ability to juxtapose these infectious, dance-worthy melodies with poignant, hard-hitting lyrics. With a thematic focus on heartbreak, depression, and anxiety, Last Thrill's music becomes a cathartic journey—a sonic exploration of the human experience's highs and lows.

As Darren brings his personal experiences and emotions to life through Last Thrill, each track becomes a testament to resilience and self-expression. In a world where synth-pop meets raw vulnerability, Last Thrill stands as a testament to the enduring power of music to connect and heal.

Last Thrill's journey unfolds on Soundcloud, where demos, previews, remixes, and covers offer a glimpse into the creative laboratory where musical magic takes shape. Enquiries can be directed to d@rrenpop.com

glasgow.name: Nick Callaghan
glasgow.description:
Hailing from Scotland, one of the worlds fastest growing countries for emerging EDM  acts wee introduce to you one particular artist who is at the forefront of a healthy batch of fresh talent within the UK, Nick Callaghan.

‘Nick Callaghan’ a naturally gifted & genuine talent who possesses a dual passion for both DJ performance and music production from Glasgow, Scotland is a name that has made an impact within the underground music scene over the years. Nick has proven his worth within the industry by injecting a rush of high-octane, fresh, original music to our ears & onto dance floors / festivals all over the world.

From Nick's early years as a budding music producer he found his productions receiving consistent support from the legendary Judge Jules on his coveted BBC Radio 1 show. Slowly but surely over the years, along with Nick's friend & production partner Will Atkinson, they together mastered the art of producing a unique style of energetic music to the highest standard. As a result of all the hard work, time and effort dedicated towards music production over the past 15 years you can now find Nick's tracks being signed to the most reputable labels in the world such as; 'Armada', 'Future sound of Egypt', 'Spinnin records', 'Kearnage', & 'Blackhole recordings', amongst many more. Over recent years Nick's tracks have been receiving consistent support from the likes of Armin van buuren on ASOT, Aly & fila, John O'Callaghan, Bryan Kearney and Ferry Corsten to name but a few. Nick's productions have achieved the difficult climb to the coveted No 1. spot on both the Trance and Psy-trance charts on 'Beatport' respectively, not to mention featuring consistently on a high  number of CD compilations compiled by the worlds top DJ's.

Although Nick's first love will always remain as Trance, his DJ sets entail Nick playing a diverse range of music such as; Trance, Psy-Trance, Breaks, to full fire Techno and all the way down to the groovier side of House music. Nick now pioneers his very own monthly show aptly named 'Off the Grid sessions' which reflects Nicks diverse and in-depth musical background where he consistently digs deep to showcase fresh and unique music for the listeners. Nick stands by his musical philosophy within his DJ sets & 'Off the grid' show where he adapts an open-mind & firmly outlines; "Good music is good music regardless of tempo, genre or age". His vigorous presence and performance behind the decks are well known for injecting energy, diversity and an electrifying atmosphere amongst the crowd whilst performing live in places such as; the UK, North America, South America & Europe. 

Nick Callaghan is without doubt one of the UK’s rising stars, when it comes to underground & energetic dance music, with his hard work reflected throughout his productions and DJ sets only emphasises the time and effort he dedicates towards the love of music! His two handed approach towards both his DJ performances and productions has set in motion an electronic music career that has him installed within the forefront of the global underground dance music scene. You can be rest assured that his unique style of music will be tearing up dance floors around the world for years to come.

If you would like to get in contact with Nick in regards to Bookings, Engineering dates / 'In-studio' tutorials or remix requests please get intouch via:

nickcallaghan-music@hotmail.co.uk

If you wish to submit promos to Nick please include a direct link to your track with full contact information in either HQ 320kbps .mp3 or .WAV format via:

nickcallaghan-music@hotmail.co.uk

Please note:
All submissions may be supported & aired by Nick on his 'Off the Grid sessions' show or featured within Nick's forthcoming live sets or guest mixes. If you insist that your material remain for internal use only and not for public performance then please make this clear within your submissions. Illegal submissions will not be supported.

Thanks.

glasgow.name: Richie Stephen
glasgow.description:
DJing on and off since around 1994.
Like many, started off by getting into the Hardcore scene and played at small local raves.
Reached the semi-final of a national DJ Comp around 2003 and subsequently played club nights in Glasgow with the likes of John 00 Fleming, Kevin Saunderson and Scot Project headlining.
Had a brief residency at Ice (Expo) Kilmarnock, supporting Mark Sherry in the process.
After a long hiatus, now getting back in the game.
Primarily Trance.

glasgow.name: Atlas Cedar
glasgow.description:
Hi, I'm Chris and I am a research scientist by day and a songwriter in my spare time. I joined SC in 2013 and I mainly record acoustic guitar and vocal harmonies, but also like playing electric guitar, bass, keyboards and using drum loops.

My musical influences include Syd Barrett, Neil Young, Peter Gabriel and Paul Simon, and increasingly fellow SoundClouders; My favourite bands include Yes, Supertramp, Pink Floyd, Rush and Steely Dan, and I also listen a lot to The Beatles, Elton John, The Who, Van Morrison, Genesis, King Crimson,  Jethro Tull, Sparks, Stevie Wonder, The Grateful Dead to name but a few...

Anyway, please feel free to get in touch - I can make any tracks (in whole or in part) available if you want them for collaborative reasons, or if you just want them for your mp3 collection :)

glasgow.name: LabourTALK

Welcome to the LabourTALK Podcast. This podcast is produced by Glasgow Pollok Constituency Labour Party (CLP) member John Beattie.

Subscribe for interviews from various Labour Party personnel discussing the current and relevant political issues from all levels of governance, including Local Authority, Scottish Parliament and Westminster.

This is not an official Labour Party podcast. It is produced by Labour Party members to put forward progressive ideas and promote Labour Party policy, values and activities. 

Join us in the Labour Party: https://join.labour.org.uk

glasgow.name: Ros T
glasgow.description:
For bookings contact: info@djrost.com
MGMT: joel@strategicmusicmanagement.com

"Ros T has gained support over the years from Annie Mac, Pete Tong, Danny Howard, Sarah Story, Shereen Cutty, Jenny Greene, Radio 1, BBC Introducing, Kiss FM, DJ Mag, Fatboy Slim, Joris Voorn, The Martinez Brothers, Purple Disco Machine & Mark Knight to name a few. Having previously released on the notorious NYC Nervous/Nurvous Records & Dutch label Altra Moda Music and amassed over 12 million streams working with Franky Rizardo on 2 previous hits, Ros T is now releasing his debut album "Teach Me" on the amazing Perfect Havoc. All things are clearly heading in the right direction for this guy. Other collabs to note are the likes of underground legend Austin Ato for Ros's track "Giving It Up", which shows the versatility and spread of Ros T's music. From his intriguing disco & soul sampling work to his full ham emotive house originals that capture a different audience, he's truly got something for everyone."
